{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01P2hFeQxYsFxEzTMbUZxR8Z","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\"results\":\"# Search Results for: MCAP format ADP synthetic data surround view\\n\\n## Messages (10 results)\\n### Result 1 of 10\\nChannel: #project-vizkit_for_sds (ID: C0A5LDVR1KP)\\nFrom: Dharmin Shah (ID: U063EQJJBFD) \\nTime: 2026-04-28 07:42:40 PDT\\nMessage_ts: 1777387360.669839\\nPermalink: [link](https:\\/\\/grid-appliedint.enterprise.slack.com\\/archives\\/C0A5LDVR1KP\\/p1777387360669839?thread_ts=1777300853.767969&cid=C0A5LDVR1KP)\\nText: \\nThanks <@U04VAS9A1PH|Young> <@U0AA23AMS04|Theo> for your inputs. I have some comments on it which you could help clarify\\n> For MCAPs your goal is basically to translate your data types, into <https:\\/\\/github.com\\/AppliedIntuition\\/applied3\\/blob\\/master\\/adp\\/services\\/playback\\/proto\\/visual_data.proto|vizkit types>, each transform is typically different due to each customer having different data types for their internal data\\n\\nI see, I was under the impression that we are using mcap conversion as an intermediate source to visualize data in vizkit. This is the workflow that was implemented for 2 customers so far.\\n\\nWhat we are doing is taking the customer specific transform directly during the ingestion, and not at the mcap layer. This means that the mcap already sees the converted ADP data format.\\n\\n> if that data were stored in URSA, MCAPs may not be necessary\\n\\nThe data is indeed in Ursa. But as you mentioned, I was not aware that Mcap is an intermediate format that may not be needed. The main blocker is that the Playback Service's Ursa reader would need converter implementations for GenericMessage(v2::Pose) \\u2192 VisualPose, GenericMessage(ActorSensor) \\u2192 VisualAgent. The same logical transforms the MCAP generator does today, but wired into the C++ Playback Service instead of the Python Flyte task.\\n\\nHow does the core stack team deal with this now?\\n\\nIn terms of raw data from Traton, we have it stored in an S3 bucket in different formats, for camera they have jpg frames, some DDS topics containing ego pose data and actor info and lidar pcaps.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Result 2 of 10\\nChannel: #project-vizkit_for_sds (ID: C0A5LDVR1KP)\\nFrom: Theo Walton (ID: U0AA23AMS04) \\nTime: 2026-04-28 09:20:47 PDT\\nMessage_ts: 1777393247.664099\\nPermalink: [link](https:\\/\\/grid-appliedint.enterprise.slack.com\\/archives\\/C0A5LDVR1KP\\/p1777393247664099?thread_ts=1777300853.767969&cid=C0A5LDVR1KP)\\nText: \\n> I see, I was under the impression that we are using mcap conversion as an intermediate source to visualize data in vizkit. This is the workflow that was implemented for 2 customers so far.\\n> \\n> What we are doing is taking the customer specific transform directly during the ingestion, and not at the mcap layer. This means that the mcap already sees the converted ADP data format.\\nhm actually my mental model may have been off, I think you are right actually\\n\\n> How does the core stack team deal with this now?\\nI think this is where my confusion came from actually, when we first used MCAPs for the core-stack we just converted their types directly into vizkit primitives and I don't think we used any of those transforms in the MCAP layer\\n\\n-- going back to the original topic though\\n\\u2022 It sounds like you use ursa, so technically direct ursa streaming could be an option, but its not super mature atm so if you just want a robust MVP this might not be a good path forward, especially the lack of the whole MCAP conversion layer which it sounds like you use\\n\\u2022 ok, so your original question was about lidar and radar support, and you linked a MCAP generator that wasn't filling in lidar or radar data. Is your question \\\"what type can I convert lidar \\/ radar to inside the MCAP such that it works in vizkit?\\\" Or something else?\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Result 3 of 10\\nChannel: #ext-program-katana-toolchain (ID: C09LSNE9Q0Y)\\nFrom: Andrew McGovern (ID: U07AY0G968H) \\nTime: 2026-05-19 10:24:08 PDT\\nMessage_ts: 1779211448.398129\\nPermalink: [link](https:\\/\\/grid-appliedint.enterprise.slack.com\\/archives\\/C09LSNE9Q0Y\\/p1779211448398129?thread_ts=1779211410.150639&cid=C09LSNE9Q0Y)\\nText: \\nHi <@U09930W4A3H|Mooyoung Lee>, <@U09930W825D|Robert Florich>, <@U09930W2KMM|Saketh Garuda> and <@U09930W63AT|Tyler Gibson>. Ahead of the workshop tomorrow, I'd like everyone to download and install the latest version of ADP onto their local machine. Could you all go to the <https:\\/\\/home.applied.co\\/downloads\\/|Downloads page> and set up ADP v1.70.44?\\n\\nThis newest version has a Synthetic Datasets feature that I would like to use in our  session tomorrow. It will allow us to export datasets from ADP in the <https:\\/\\/www.nuscenes.org\\/nuscenes#data-format|Nuscenes format>, which will making model training\\/testing pipelines easier to create\\n\\nI look forward to seeing you all tomorrow on the call!\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Result 4 of 10\\nChannel: #proposal-traton-lynxion-adas-next-gen (ID: C08PRQQPRCM)\\nFrom: Adrian Nadi (ID: U05KJK5AASH) \\nTime: 2025-06-30 06:30:19 PDT\\nMessage_ts: 1751290219.579609\\nReply count: 3\\nPermalink: [link](https:\\/\\/grid-appliedint.enterprise.slack.com\\/archives\\/C08PRQQPRCM\\/p1751290219579609?thread_ts=1751290219.579609&cid=C08PRQQPRCM)\\nText: \\n:thread: ADP :holographic-adp:  work \\u2013 Lynxion release 3, sprint 2 (ends July 18)\\nHey folks - I\\u2019ve allocated the following tasks for this 3-week sprint. Please review, flag any blockers and add any additional tasks under the story\\/epic if needed.\\n\\n\\u2022 <https:\\/\\/jiratoolchain.collaborationlayer-traton.com\\/browse\\/LYNXION-964|LYNXION-964> - Integrate ADP synthetic sensor simulation to be able to pass data as a seamless replacement for the real-cameras - <@U07U3KT03MG|SaiP>\\n\\u2022 <https:\\/\\/jiratoolchain.collaborationlayer-traton.com\\/browse\\/LYNXION-966|LYNXION-966> - Create an ADP customer interface which is able to publish the synthetic sensor data on DDS (Synapse) and then run a recorder to store the data in a file (MCAP format). <@U07U3KT03MG|SaiP>\\n\\u2022 <https:\\/\\/jiratoolchain.collaborationlayer-traton.com\\/browse\\/LYNXION-965|LYNXION-965> - Prepare a calibration file with the correct extrinsics and intrinsics matching the setup of the synthetic data. - unassigned :bust_in_silhouette:\\n\\u2022 <https:\\/\\/jiratoolchain.collaborationlayer-traton.com\\/browse\\/LYNXION-1095|LYNXION-1095> - Enable access to the ATS ADP cluster for the Next Gen ADAS team - <@U038F3R0TQF|Rasmus> \\n\\n---\\n\\n### Result 5 of 10\\nChannel: #eng-axion-mission-control (ID: C0940HQ2UG6)\\nFrom: Jordan Millard (ID: U085L0TJ7ED) \\nTime: 2026-05-13 13:51:29 PDT\\nMessage_ts: 1778705489.560449\\nReply count: 3\\nPermalink: [link](https:\\/\\/grid-appliedint.enterprise.slack.com\\/archives\\/C0940HQ2UG6\\/p1778705489560449?thread_ts=1778705489.560449&cid=C0940HQ2UG6)\\nText: \\n:thread: Another visual question, more about the original MCAP conversion setup\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Result 6 of 10\\nChannel: #ext-jcatechnologies (ID: C068LLG749W)\\nFrom: Fengkai Chen (ID: U088X63BUTS) \\nTime: 2026-03-31 16:55:07 PDT\\nMessage_ts: 1775001307.974119\\nPermalink: [link](https:\\/\\/grid-appliedint.enterprise.slack.com\\/archives\\/C068LLG749W\\/p1775001307974119?thread_ts=1774908673.568909&cid=C068LLG749W)\\nText: \\nPlease ignore the unrelated container :lolsob:\\n```docker ps --format \\\"{{.Names}}\\\"\\njcatechnologies_applied_bridge\\ncompassionate_curie\\nexciting_allen\\namazing_haslett\\nadp_vehiclesim\\nadp_usage\\nadp_ursa\\nadp_test_management\\nadp_synthetic_datasets\\nadp_sim_data\\nadp_sensor_sim\\nadp_schema_registry\\nadp_scenario_library\\nadp_plans\\nadp_neural_rendering\\nadp_mission_sim\\nadp_mission_control\\nadp_maps\\nadp_insights\\nadp_edge_mlops\\nadp_dora\\nadp_datasets\\nadp_copilot\\nadp_config\\nadp_batches\\nadp_async_jobs\\nadp_accounts\\nadp_abstract_scenarios\\ncrazy_dubinsky\\npractical_euler\\nadoring_yalow\\nadp\\nadp_pg\\nsim_cart\\napplied3_dev\\napplied3_dev_pg```\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Result 7 of 10\\nChannel: #program-komatsu-surround-view-system (ID: C08K6CTGCDS)\\nFrom: Alex Del Re (ID: U063Y6FQA5V) \\nTime: 2026-05-14 10:06:19 PDT\\nMessage_ts: 1778778379.521759\\nPermalink: [link](https:\\/\\/grid-appliedint.enterprise.slack.com\\/archives\\/C08K6CTGCDS\\/p1778778379521759?thread_ts=1778778190.753099&cid=C08K6CTGCDS)\\nText: \\n<@U09DVKBSKMZ|Sohum> , discussing with <@U07AY0G968H|Andrew McGovern> the convo (<https:\\/\\/grid-appliedint.enterprise.slack.com\\/archives\\/D07E5HPJFM2|notes>) y'all had on ADP integration for Synthetic Data. A few open questions I have are:\\n\\u2022 how your team evaluates the SVS model performance? What is the workflow to address misclassification seen by the system? \\n\\u2022 How are those misclassifications currently identified? \\n\\u2022 What are your current data sources?\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Result 8 of 10\\nChannel: #proposal-bmw-tooling (ID: C09C3FPJXSB)\\nFrom: Noam Rand (ID: U07QDE85QBY) \\nTime: 2026-04-14 09:30:59 PDT\\nMessage_ts: 1776184259.703329\\nPermalink: [link](https:\\/\\/grid-appliedint.enterprise.slack.com\\/archives\\/C09C3FPJXSB\\/p1776184259703329?thread_ts=1776183787.652529&cid=C09C3FPJXSB)\\nText: \\nWhat we can concretely show now\\n\\u2022 Per-run YAML-driven ingestion entry point: a YAML that comes with each drive\\/run and tells the system key ingestion inputs like code version, where to find the MCAP\\/log files, and run tags\\/metadata.\\n\\u2022 <https:\\/\\/neuron.oci.applied.dev\\/ursa\\/workflows\\/post-upload|ADP\\/UI view of workflow execution + metadata:> show the workflow\\/dashboard and drive details page to illustrate post-upload phases, run metadata, and how quality \\/ processing steps are tracked.\\nHow to position sensor-agnostic \\/ multi-config support\\n\\u2022 Today: we do not yet have fully config-only support for arbitrary sensor suites and data formats; cars and trucks still use separate codepaths today.\\n\\u2022 What exists \\/ is in progress: there is active work to commonize this via the FrameGenerationPlatform ABC, with platform-specific implementations like OnroadPlatform and TruckingGen2Platform, so the same pipeline can handle different vehicle types by swapping the platform implementation.\\n\\u2022 Good concrete example to show: contrast current car vs truck sensor definitions (onroad\\/...\\/data_constants.py vs trucking\\/...\\/sensor_topics.py) and explain that this is what is being abstracted behind the new platform layer.\\nHow to answer BMW on multiple formats \\/ synthetic data\\n\\u2022 Current state: MCAP is the clearest supported format to talk through today.\\n\\u2022 Forward-looking answer: the architecture is moving toward a generalized \\u201c<https:\\/\\/docs.google.com\\/document\\/d\\/1AD_4yWlxYdpABrMbh_bzyjVZDnlPlVtO5j3sLgW5v5U\\/edit?usp=drive_link|comprehension\\u201d \\/ abstraction layer> so downstream tooling can operate across different log formats and sensor configurations, including sim\\/synthetic data, but that story is still work in progress, not something to oversell as fully productized today.\\n\\n<@U07UYPQ5VL1|Abhay> shared <https:\\/\\/docs.google.com\\/document\\/d\\/1yyk149vIoB537ghYS7BFQ8CJtJVgfTwhzMcQ0j75fgA\\/edit?tab=t.0|this>.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Result 9 of 10\\nChannel: #eng-sensor_simulation (ID: CP0005VLK)\\nFrom: Jansen Thorogood (ID: U023G2ABKSS) \\nTime: 2026-05-19 11:07:37 PDT\\nMessage_ts: 1779214057.919319\\nPermalink: [link](https:\\/\\/grid-appliedint.enterprise.slack.com\\/archives\\/CP0005VLK\\/p1779214057919319?thread_ts=1779205679.928339&cid=CP0005VLK)\\nText: \\n<@U0A36QNT2UT|Chunshu> I downloaded their .mcap files, I'm looking to learn how I can visualize the data in those files and then make my own to do an A\\/B comparison between synthetic and real data.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Result 10 of 10\\nChannel: #program-komatsu-eng (ID: C09651DRWJE)\\nFrom: Alex Del Re (ID: U063Y6FQA5V) \\nTime: 2026-04-23 15:46:38 PDT\\nMessage_ts: 1776984398.901909\\nPermalink: [link](https:\\/\\/grid-appliedint.enterprise.slack.com\\/archives\\/C09651DRWJE\\/p1776984398901909?thread_ts=1776984393.946539&cid=C09651DRWJE)\\nText: \\n<@U056B308XB2|Ting>, following up from my sync with Brian White yesterday. He mentioned you two chatted about the Komatsu synthetic data ML integration and that you took an action item to scope what's possible with synthetic interfaces and compatibility with existing ML infrastructure.\\n\\nA few things I wanted to get your take on:\\n\\u2022 What came out of your conversation with Brian in terms of ML scoping? He said there's precedent for this kind of workflow (he mentioned a US gov pattern) but it would require infra work not currently allocated to the Komatsu teams.\\n\\u2022 What would it actually look like to consume synthetic data output and feed it into the ODS pipeline? We need to make sure the output format is something ODS can ingest.\\n\\u2022 How do we want to evaluate model performance? I mentioned IoU as one option that has ADP support already, but want to align on this before we go further. Brian mentioned he is looking to Applied for guidance\\ncc <@U07AY0G968H|Andrew McGovern>\\n\\n---\\n\\n\",\"pagination_info\":\"For the next page of results use cursor `Q1VSUkVOVF9QQUdFOjI=`\\n\"}"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01AeQvEvhszVJhWytvQBSm5n","session_id":"e608aebc-1e8f-4a54-bfcc-c9052cb98c4e","uuid":"02f8c51f-7a9c-45ca-bd7f-620fdd30bf44","timestamp":"2026-06-01T17:05:26.022Z","subagent_type":"general-purpose","task_description":"Research ROSbag/MCAP format for ADP pipeline"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01GNyLHutsQKvWZz1yRZP9Qf","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\"results\":\"# Search Results for: ROSbag topics ADP perception pipeline\\n\\n## Messages (10 results)\\n### Result 1 of 10\\nChannel: #eng-sds-perception (ID: C0666GRNPUG)\\nFrom: Punit Tulpule (ID: U08P0S35E74) \\nTime: 2026-05-19 13:26:00 PDT\\nMessage_ts: 1779222360.626479\\nPermalink: [link](https:\\/\\/grid-appliedint.enterprise.slack.com\\/archives\\/C0666GRNPUG\\/p1779222360626479?thread_ts=1779222260.454839&cid=C0666GRNPUG)\\nText: \\n:rocket: *New: Logsim-based Perception Eval Dashboard is live!*\\n\\n:link: <https:\\/\\/pet.experimental.apps.applied.dev\\/>\\n:point_right: Want to try it right away? Use batch ID *154717* (last night's cut)\\n\\nVisualize perception results (precision, recall, etc.) from your logsim runs that have ground truth labels\\u2014 sliced by actor type, perception regions around ego, and ODD conditions like fog, rain, intersections, and more.\\n\\nWhat you can do:\\n\\u2022 View perception metrics as an *aggregate* across a batch,\\n\\u2022  Single run metrics (with direct links to the sim runs from the single-run view)\\n\\u2022  Run *ODD coverage analysis*\\n\\u2022 Filter by actors, perception regions around ego, and ODD conditions\\n\\nHow to use it:\\nDrop in a batch ID from your open-loop-perception logsim run in ADP and the dashboard pulls the metrics for you.\\n\\nWho it helps:\\n\\u2022 *ML model owners* \\u2014 show clear progress vs. past models\\n\\u2022 *Sys-eng* \\u2014 track daily progression \\/ catch regressions\\n\\u2022 *Everyone* \\u2014 compare models across domains\\n\\nThe perception eval pipeline includes -\\n\\u2022 ODD tagged set of eval logsims in master frontier-scenarios-workspace\\n\\u2022 Perception metric computation using metrics manager\\n\\u2022 VT type querry engine\\n\\u2022 Vibe-coded UI\\n\\nNext steps:\\n\\u2022 Add other metrics like track length\\n\\u2022 Add other perception functions like traffic light detection\\/traffic sign detection etc.\\n\\u2022 Add sys-eng requirements or MTBF relation\\nGive it a try and let me know what you think!  :raised_hands:\\ncc <@U062ZV5ABC3|BrianZ>, <@U045GK7N6H4|Vickram>, <@U07QS047N9H|Tianyuan>, <@U098U01TF3P|Robert Cosgriff> <@U063NKNGAAC|Prem>\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Result 2 of 10\\nChannel: #ext-program-katana-toolchain (ID: C09LSNE9Q0Y)\\nFrom: Andrew McGovern (ID: U07AY0G968H) \\nTime: 2026-06-01 09:22:31 PDT\\nMessage_ts: 1780330951.672899\\nPermalink: [link](https:\\/\\/grid-appliedint.enterprise.slack.com\\/archives\\/C09LSNE9Q0Y\\/p1780330951672899?thread_ts=1780322410.292029&cid=C09LSNE9Q0Y)\\nText: \\nDiscussed live, notes from conversation here:\\n\\u2022 Data Engine pipeline still being built on on Applied side\\n\\u2022 Eventually, this ADP data will need to be written to a ROS bag. These message definitions are not yet set in stone. Once they are, we can begin converting this ADP data into ROS bag\\n\\u2022 For now, team will focus on:\\n    \\u25e6 1. Committing scripts into the vehicle-os-katana repo at \\/katana\\/katana_adp in a new folder\\n    \\u25e6 2. Generating datasets with occlusions and weather \\n\\n---\\n\\n### Result 3 of 10\\nChannel: #ext-program-katana-smart-aht (ID: C0AAQ2U5JPJ)\\nFrom: Michelle Zhang (ID: U08HUFANNHK) \\nTime: 2026-05-07 14:49:06 PDT\\nMessage_ts: 1778190546.394369\\nPermalink: [link](https:\\/\\/grid-appliedint.enterprise.slack.com\\/archives\\/C0AAQ2U5JPJ\\/p1778190546394369?thread_ts=1778020608.498259&cid=C0AAQ2U5JPJ)\\nText: \\nThe Perception pipeline is described in the <https:\\/\\/miro.com\\/app\\/board\\/uXjVGBZsB64=\\/|Miro board>'s Smart AHT Perception Architecture tab.\\ncc <@U099CFQ3PL6|Aravind APS> <@U09930VBC9M|Urara>\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Result 4 of 10\\nChannel: #code-reviews-data-and-ml-platform (ID: C0699PDNFCL)\\nFrom: Tim Stanke (ID: U07F02DQ72M) \\nTime: 2026-05-22 08:50:24 PDT\\nMessage_ts: 1779465024.888659\\nPermalink: [link](https:\\/\\/grid-appliedint.enterprise.slack.com\\/archives\\/C0699PDNFCL\\/p1779465024888659?thread_ts=1779394063.898689&cid=C0699PDNFCL)\\nText: \\n<@U05MF8HMRLN|Yi Sheng> this is prototyping an ADP-RL pipeline in APX, would appreciate if I can get feedback on it today :prayge:\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Result 5 of 10\\nChannel: #eng-data-engine (ID: C06632KLGPM)\\nFrom: Abhay Vardhan (ID: U07UYPQ5VL1) \\nTime: 2026-05-13 18:14:47 PDT\\nMessage_ts: 1778721287.710019\\nPermalink: [link](https:\\/\\/grid-appliedint.enterprise.slack.com\\/archives\\/C06632KLGPM\\/p1778721287710019?thread_ts=1778610807.177519&cid=C06632KLGPM)\\nText: \\nNotes from the plant review:\\n\\nMay 13, 2026 | <https:\\/\\/www.google.com\\/calendar\\/event?eid=MTZmcDRiOTR1Z2c4ZzEwM3VwNG1sdmtzajQgYWJoYXkudmFyZGhhbkBhcHBsaWVkLmNv|Mini plant review for trucking ADR>\\nAttendees: <mailto:abhay.vardhan@applied.co|Abhay Vardhan> <mailto:samser@applied.co|Sam Serpoosh> <mailto:parth@applied.co|Parth Baokar>\\n\\n\\u2022 Answered various questions about the motivation and need for the plant.\\n\\u2022 Discussed trade offs between reading all mcaps with a topic group at the same time vs doing them individually (alternative design)\\n\\u2022 Discussion on whether we can defer reading from different mcaps and instead stick to having a different topic group for each lidar sensor (4 lidar topic groups vs 1 lidar topic group containing all the lidar sensors)\\n    \\u25e6 Benefit is that each group lives entirely within one sensor bag directory, so the existing ADR machinery (no cut-point logic, no cross-bag merging) works as-is.\\n    \\u25e6 Tradeoff is that when hydrating a perception input entity that consumes all AT360 lidars, the hydration layer must make 4 separate object store calls instead of 1. However, batch hydration amortizes this cost: across a batch of N frames, the number of object store calls is still 4 (one per group), not 4N. The per-call overhead therefore does not grow with batch size.\\n\\u2022 Decision:\\n    \\u25e6 Go with having different lidar topic groups for each lidar sensor for now. The design is vastly simpler. The performance tradeoff is acceptable. Furthermore, the decision is easily reversible: if in future we decide to start grouping the lidars together, we can do so in a forward fill manner without much changes on the client side.\\n\\nAlso discussed separately with <@U09545J6V5W|Cyrus> <@U09BBC3MB3R|sOOOdhana> <@U01TY8J1Y05|RyanB> and the decision to go with different lidar topic groups is acceptable for now. This can be revisited later if performance becomes an issue.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Result 6 of 10\\nChannel: #tmp-ml-rl-code-health (ID: C0AB5EG6NKD)\\nFrom: Colby Duke (ID: U05C189H3B8) \\nTime: 2026-03-18 14:43:19 PDT\\nMessage_ts: 1773870199.787049\\nPermalink: [link](https:\\/\\/grid-appliedint.enterprise.slack.com\\/archives\\/C0AB5EG6NKD\\/p1773870199787049?thread_ts=1773778935.755629&cid=C0AB5EG6NKD)\\nText: \\ncurrent reconstruction pipeline writes to onroad-perception-datasets, new reconstruction pipeline writes to neuron prod ADP buckets\\n\\ncurrent eval pipeline pulls data through \\\"legacy\\\" nre gs observation class from onroad-perception-datasets, new eval pipeline pulls data through the new eval interface from neuron prod ADP buckets\\n\\nso you reconstruct AND run eval on a given set of reconstructions with the current reconstruction + eval pipelines, and then repeat for the new ones. two parallel executions, both with two subtasks.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Result 7 of 10\\nChannel: #program-fordotosan-tools (ID: CPQSX9NL9)\\nFrom: Maresa Fees (ID: U08JP4J1TSS) \\nTime: 2026-02-13 04:44:04 PST\\nMessage_ts: 1770986644.740039\\nPermalink: [link](https:\\/\\/grid-appliedint.enterprise.slack.com\\/archives\\/CPQSX9NL9\\/p1770986644740039?thread_ts=1770985575.853459&cid=CPQSX9NL9)\\nText: \\nFull Notes <https:\\/\\/docs.google.com\\/document\\/d\\/14DLoEwXRpll4vke9DnnpXIJqqTea_SOnN3wZlLNCGcU\\/edit?tab=t.0|here>\\n\\nStatus SiL\\/HiL\\n\\u2022 SiL Interface Status: Furkan is currently successfully integrating ETAS FMUs and working on time Synchronization\\n\\u2022 checking on how much they can then reuse the sil interface for hil (cc <@U07U3KT03MG|SaiP>) \\n\\u2022 Status Update for object HiL capabilities --> <@U07U3KT03MG|SaiP> to update\\n\\u2022 Hardware Constraints: The TI board development remains the primary bottleneck for them to currently even use ObjectHiL;\\n\\u2022 Sensor &amp; Radars are also not decided for Sensor HiL Scoping\\n\\u2022 Possibility of HiL Replay? (CC:<@U036QNN2667|AniR>) \\n\\u2022 Camera HiL - they are waiting for a quote from ZF before asking us (CC: <@U036QNN2667|AniR>) \\n\\nTesting Priorities:\\n\\u2022 Object HiL (Priority 1): This is the highest priority, to get this back to a working state and will require updated ARXML files to accommodate new ground truth data.\\n\\u2022 Sensor Fusion (Priority 2): Focusing on AEB functions using a configuration of one camera and four radars but with only the object sensors.\\n\\u2022 Sensor HiL (Priority 3): \\n\\nADP Use Cases\\n\\u2022 Data Explorer is in use with the Highway Pilot motion planning logs. No perception currently. \\n\\u2022 Primarily utilizing Rosbag replay for with perception \\n\\u2022 Future Ingestion ideas: Future use cases could involve ingesting perception and camera data into Data Explorer to eventually support a Resimulation pipeline.\\n\\u2022 Blocker: The team does not yet know the file format  (maybe MDF4) and also the truck is not collecting data currently.\\n\\nBiggest Pain Points:\\n\\u2022 Sim-to-Real Gap: While 3D environments and HD maps are used for synthetic traffic, it is not enough for them. \\n\\u2022 Noise Injection Pain Point: They are not happy with realistic sensor noise at the object level for fusion tracking, which will requires more deep-dive.\\n\\nAction Items &amp; Next Steps\\n\\u2022 <@U08JP4J1TSS|Maresa>: Schedule a meeting next week to review detailed timelines that Didem wants to share across all workstreams.\\n\\u2022 <@U07U3KT03MG|SaiP> on giving more context on what is missing for the requirements list that was shared\\n\\u2022 Didem: Share specific sensor data file formats so Applied can propose solutions for perception data ingestion.\\n\\u2022 Didem: Check internally whether resimulation could be followed up on\\n\\nCC:<@U036QNN2667|AniR>\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Result 8 of 10\\nChannel: #eng-data-engine (ID: C06632KLGPM)\\nFrom: Andrew McGovern (ID: U07AY0G968H) \\nTime: 2026-05-20 10:16:59 PDT\\nMessage_ts: 1779297419.006539\\nPermalink: [link](https:\\/\\/grid-appliedint.enterprise.slack.com\\/archives\\/C06632KLGPM\\/p1779297419006539?thread_ts=1779297415.281679&cid=C06632KLGPM)\\nText: \\nKomatsu is interested in using our data engine model training pipeline. They want to do this\\n\\n1. Generate synthetic data with ADP - they already know how to do this well\\n2. Use that data to edit an existing perception model for object detection\\n3. Run the perception model on real and\\/or synthetic data\\n\\nI've been working with <@U056B308XB2|Ting> so far on this, but not sure what the model pipelines around it actually look like. What does a model training deployment for a customer look like?\\n\\ncc <@U063Y6FQA5V|AlexD>\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Result 9 of 10\\nChannel: #program-traton-tools (ID: CHXNDRD4J)\\nFrom: Jonas Wittmann (ID: U06MKU9MZT8) \\nTime: 2026-05-29 03:12:11 PDT\\nMessage_ts: 1780049531.790119\\nPermalink: [link](https:\\/\\/grid-appliedint.enterprise.slack.com\\/archives\\/CHXNDRD4J\\/p1780049531790119?thread_ts=1780045059.003079&cid=CHXNDRD4J)\\nText: \\n\\u2022 On Slide 9 and 10, you propose the two different approaches. As \\\"shared library approach\\\" is currently not supported on the cluster (<https:\\/\\/applied-tools.slack.com\\/archives\\/C017WFP5020\\/p1774954945087729|here>), I would limit the discussion to the \\\"normal approach\\\" for now. Increasing the efficiency with the shared library approach could be done on-demand at a later stage and would then require some eng effort on our side. <-- these specifics on the implementation might be too detailed if the Ouster engineers sees it the first time. The slides and comparison are great though :nice-2: \\n\\u2022 It would be interesting to know if they already have a C++ model of the specific lidar\\/the perception pipeline that they can reuse for such a plugin architecture\\n\\u2022 We had shared the following engagement proposal with Traton: <https:\\/\\/appliedintuition.sharepoint.com\\/:b:\\/s\\/ext-scania\\/IQDL5GBaAl47RI-_w36N2jH-AT_9emw7gt7ayabP72Z9JDo?e=vYDHrq|Engagement Model Proposal .pdf> --> We should share some expectation from our side such as \\\"you would run the ADP simulator to develop the plugin\\\"\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Result 10 of 10\\nChannel: #temp-close-log-sim-sim-to-real-gap (ID: C0AGEBBJG6Q)\\nFrom: Adi Varshney (ID: U034JPWUNSD) \\nTime: 2026-03-25 14:23:48 PDT\\nMessage_ts: 1774473828.948949\\nPermalink: [link](https:\\/\\/grid-appliedint.enterprise.slack.com\\/archives\\/C0AGEBBJG6Q\\/p1774473828948949?thread_ts=1774473656.437779&cid=C0AGEBBJG6Q)\\nText: \\nif folks are already looking at this can we:\\n1. confirm detections are being reported by the stack\\n    a. if no, perception stack is unable to produce the required info -> input\\/platform\\/stack sw issue\\n        i. are lidar topics 1:1 with the bag data (check timestamps)\\n        ii. is gpu 1:1? run bag looper\\n        iii. is model the same? confirm with <@U045GK7N6H4|VickrOOOm> \\n    b. if yes, confirm tracks are reported by the stack\\n        i. if no, stack issue or issue in passing info from perception to object tracking\\n        ii. if yes, confirm that interface can report tracked objects correctly\\n            1. if no, integration issue\\n            2. if yes, adp issue\\n\\n---\\n\\n\",\"pagination_info\":\"For the next page of results use cursor `Q1VSUkVOVF9QQUdFOjI=`\\n\"}"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01AeQvEvhszVJhWytvQBSm5n","session_id":"e608aebc-1e8f-4a54-bfcc-c9052cb98c4e","uuid":"59054496-44ae-4a8f-beae-ac7e0689173c","timestamp":"2026-06-01T17:05:26.890Z","subagent_type":"general-purpose","task_description":"Research ROSbag/MCAP format for ADP pipeline"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01FcMfNEhHvJq3pGhLLWvS2y","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\"results\":\"# Search Results for: data engine ADP synthetic data format\\n\\n## Messages (10 results)\\n### Result 1 of 10\\nChannel: #program-komatsu (ID: C0961E7856J)\\nFrom: Alex Del Re (ID: U063Y6FQA5V) \\nTime: 2026-05-12 09:29:48 PDT\\nMessage_ts: 1778603388.421509\\nPermalink: [link](https:\\/\\/grid-appliedint.enterprise.slack.com\\/archives\\/C0961E7856J\\/p1778603388421509?thread_ts=1778515479.425979&cid=C0961E7856J)\\nText: \\nVirtual Toolchain \\n\\u2022 :status_green: Deliver Developer Studio SIL virtualizations to enable inter-zonal testing for Autolube and Engine Interface applications\\n    \\u25e6 Planning to host Peoria SIL testing workshop next week for autolube testing\\n\\u2022 :large_yellow_circle: Integrate SVS software with ADP sensor simulations\\n    \\u25e6 <@U07AY0G968H|Andrew McGovern> going to meet in <@U09DVKBSKMZ|Sohum> to discuss process\\n\\u2022 :status_green: Enhance the CI\\/CD pipeline to accelerate developer velocity, improving reliability, and enable consistent resource access\\n    \\u25e6 Added upstream back to core-stack functionality\\n    \\u25e6 adding workbench CI testing \\n\\u2022 :large_yellow_circle: Enable Machine Learning team to generate synthetic data &amp; evaluate performance change on ODS on oblique angle scenarios\\n    \\u25e6 Scoping a synthetic datasets workshop for next week\\n    \\u25e6 Planning to discuss with <@U06EB2G5EGM|Sergey> on Data Engine pipeline options for Komatsu team\\n\\u2022 :status_green: Validate synthetic sensors with Komatsu lab data to understand object detection metrics in different environmental conditions\\n    \\u25e6 <@U07AY0G968H|Andrew McGovern> reviewing with sensor validation team to discuss \\n\\u2022 :status_green: Develop 830E TruckSim model to enable Smart AHT controls simulation testing\\n    \\u25e6 Received 830E model parameters and working with TruckSim to team to create braking model for SDV SW application testing\\n    \\u25e6 Steering model development will occur after the braking model\\n\\u2022 :large_yellow_circle: Define plan to integrate 930E TruckSim model with steering and braking applications for SDV SW team\\n    \\u25e6 Planning to start this during 2026.21 sprint\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Result 2 of 10\\nChannel: #program-komatsu (ID: C0961E7856J)\\nFrom: Alex Del Re (ID: U063Y6FQA5V) \\nTime: 2026-05-19 08:40:21 PDT\\nMessage_ts: 1779205221.762099\\nPermalink: [link](https:\\/\\/grid-appliedint.enterprise.slack.com\\/archives\\/C0961E7856J\\/p1779205221762099?thread_ts=1779120287.921819&cid=C0961E7856J)\\nText: \\nVirtual Toolchain \\n\\u2022 :status_green: Deliver Developer Studio SIL virtualizations to enable inter-zonal testing for Autolube and Engine Interface applications\\n    \\u25e6 Hosting Peoria SIL test workshop week of 2206.21 for autolube testing\\n\\u2022 :large_yellow_circle: Integrate SVS software with ADP sensor simulations\\n    \\u25e6 Focus for SVS integration will be synthetic datasets integration into SVS training pipeline. \\n    \\u25e6 Going to discuss with <@U06EB2G5EGM|Sergey> on Data Engine pipeline options for Komatsu team this sprint\\n\\u2022 :status_green: Enhance the CI\\/CD pipeline to accelerate developer velocity, improving reliability, and enable consistent resource access\\n    \\u25e6 adding workbench CI testing based on outputs from Peoria workshop\\n    \\u25e6 going to release first proposal for katana repo release process this sprint \\n\\u2022 :status_green: Enable Machine Learning team to generate synthetic data &amp; evaluate performance change on ODS on oblique angle scenarios\\n    \\u25e6 <@U07AY0G968H|Andrew McGovern> to host SD workshop with ML team this week\\n\\u2022 :status_green: Validate synthetic sensors with Komatsu lab data to understand object detection metrics in different environmental conditions\\n    \\u25e6 <@U07AY0G968H|Andrew McGovern> reviewing with sensor validation team to discuss \\n\\u2022 :large_yellow_circle: Develop 830E TruckSim model to enable Smart AHT controls simulation testing\\n    \\u25e6 <@U0A0B3GJSJX|Jeff Moran> - Komatsu told us they are no longer interested in simulation capabilities for the 830E, but rather the 830PA. \\n\\u2022 :large_yellow_circle: \\/ :red_circle: Define plan to integrate 930E TruckSim model with steering and braking applications for SDV SW team\\n    \\u25e6 <@U0A0B3GJSJX|Jeff Moran> - seems like the direction with Katana work-streams (SDV and SDA) is to test with TruckSim models for the 830 program for controls simulations. We originally got direction from Lee to integrate a 930 model with simulation, but seems like this is not the case. I am planning to discuss with Wes, BrianW, and JoeB on the plan for working with TruckSims this week\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Result 3 of 10\\nChannel: #eng-data-engine (ID: C06632KLGPM)\\nFrom: Andrew McGovern (ID: U07AY0G968H) \\nTime: 2026-05-20 10:16:59 PDT\\nMessage_ts: 1779297419.006539\\nPermalink: [link](https:\\/\\/grid-appliedint.enterprise.slack.com\\/archives\\/C06632KLGPM\\/p1779297419006539?thread_ts=1779297415.281679&cid=C06632KLGPM)\\nText: \\nKomatsu is interested in using our data engine model training pipeline. They want to do this\\n\\n1. Generate synthetic data with ADP - they already know how to do this well\\n2. Use that data to edit an existing perception model for object detection\\n3. Run the perception model on real and\\/or synthetic data\\n\\nI've been working with <@U056B308XB2|Ting> so far on this, but not sure what the model pipelines around it actually look like. What does a model training deployment for a customer look like?\\n\\ncc <@U063Y6FQA5V|AlexD>\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Result 4 of 10\\nChannel: #eng-pmt (ID: C07NE8HF3JP)\\nFrom: Adi Varshney (ID: U034JPWUNSD) \\nTime: 2026-04-22 15:39:24 PDT\\nMessage_ts: 1776897564.856869\\nReply count: 9\\nPermalink: [link](https:\\/\\/grid-appliedint.enterprise.slack.com\\/archives\\/C07NE8HF3JP\\/p1776897564856869?thread_ts=1776897564.856869&cid=C07NE8HF3JP)\\nText: \\n<!channel> Hey folks, we're cleaning channels to reduce noise and improve support on urgent\\/breaking issues (w\\/ traceability) :traceability:\\n\\n\\u2022 General questions and design reviews should go to <#C07NE8HF3JP> (so this channel)\\n\\u2022 Incidents or breakages should be reported via Slack Workflow in <#C08Q4AHG81F|core-stack-incident-reports> with priority 1, 2, or 3 (very important -- people often get confused). Running the workflow tags a DRI and creates Jira tickets to track occurrences \\/ closure.\\n\\nYour workflow options are shown in the screenshot:\\n\\u2022 Stack Tooling Breakage: issues with ADP\\/sim on any cluster\\n\\u2022 Dev Tooling Breakage: Buildkite\\/dev docker) . Running the workflow tags a DRI and creates Jira tickets to track occurrences \\/ closure.\\n\\u2022 Data Engine Breakage: Issue with flyte, registering metrics, etc.\\n\\u2022 Eval Breakage: Issue running eval or accessing eval results\\n\\u2022 Deployment Breakage: Issue deploying code to a vehicle or rig\\n\\nIf you post urgent issues in this channel :index_pointing_at_the_viewer: we'll call it out and ask that you post instead in <#C08Q4AHG81F|core-stack-incident-reports> for the reasons above.\\n\\ncc <@U05LH20HF0V|JasmineW> <@U01A53L089J|Angela> <@S096J6V3JCC|trucks-tools-swe-on-call>\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Result 5 of 10\\nChannel: #program-maymobility-tools (ID: CCZL8EF60)\\nFrom: Vikram Krishnan (ID: U08RVQS5YR2) \\nTime: 2026-04-13 08:30:22 PDT\\nMessage_ts: 1776094222.078859\\nPermalink: [link](https:\\/\\/grid-appliedint.enterprise.slack.com\\/archives\\/CCZL8EF60\\/p1776094222078859?thread_ts=1776093962.079749&cid=CCZL8EF60)\\nText: \\n\\u2022 Account Overview \\u2014 May Mobility has used Applied ADP since 2018 (second-ever Applied customer). Jonathan Voigt now overseeing data\\/infra teams (no longer directly on sim). Matt Wood (VP AIV) key stakeholder for test suites and NeuralSim. Meeting agenda: account overview, product demos (Data Engine, NeuralSim, next-gen ADP), HIL lab tour.\\n\\u2022 Digital Twin &amp; Next-Gen ADK \\u2014 Primary goal of digital twin map (Pittsfield Township, Ann Arbor) is testing new sensors, sensor locations, and positioning in sim before mounting on physical vehicles. Related to next-gen ADK planning (new compute + sensors).\\n\\u2022 Cluster Usage &amp; Sim Volume\\n    \\u25e6 Growth \\u2014 Sim volume nearly doubled: 7.8M sims in 2024 \\u2192 15M since start of 2025. January peak at 1.7M sims driven by new software branch push. 82 active users\\/month avg in 2025.\\n    \\u25e6 Parallelism \\u2014 Limit increased from 180 to 300 (free trial Feb\\u2013Mar, extended through Apr); confirmation pending for extension through Apr 2027.\\n    \\u25e6 GPU migration \\u2014 Sims shifting from CPU to GPU queues as May combines behavior + perception modules; increasing cloud costs but decreasing cost per sim hour at scale. Additional headless licenses expected to cut 22K-sim run time by ~20 min.\\n    \\u25e6 Sim duration \\u2014 Average sim length doubled from 3 min to 6 min over last 15\\u201316 months.\\n\\u2022 Cost &amp; Data Retention\\n    \\u25e6 S3 optimization \\u2014 May has internal efforts effort underway; May requested breakdown of per-sim vs per-day AWS costs (RDS, S3) to improve cost accounting.\\n    \\u25e6 Glacier \\u2014 Potential use of Glacier Instant Retrieval (~4x cheaper) for 6-month-old data; needs internal follow-up.\\n    \\u25e6 Pruning \\u2014 Front-end viz results pruned every 30 days; full sim results >6 months deleted manually.\\n\\u2022 Stability &amp; Support \\u2014 Matt Wood asked about open tickets and stabilization. Fix for large sim cancellation (>5K\\u201310K sims) deploying soon. Pylon (AI search assistant, similar to Zendesk) used for L1 triaging\\/product questions but not for high error rate issues. Follow-up: metrics dashboard on ticket burndown and resolution time.\\n\\u2022 Test Suites (NCAP 2026 AEB)\\n    \\u25e6 44 collision\\/accident avoidance scenarios available. Goal: run on May's maps with their stack in the loop.\\n    \\u25e6 Validation Toolset dashboard enables parameter sweeps over scenarios, tracking error\\/success rates to assess stack effectiveness.\\n    \\u25e6 Next steps: share scenario spreadsheet, deploy trial examples on May cluster (Applied stack + map first), then integrate May's stack\\/map.\\n    \\u25e6 Challenge: map conversion \\u2014 suggested using OpenDRIVE as intermediate format to simplify import. Mark Jones is primary contact for test suite integration.\\n\\u2022 Data Engine &amp; Data Explorer\\n    \\u25e6 Architecture \\u2014 Data flywheel: ingest \\u2192 enrich (autolabel, scene tags, 80+ QC metrics) \\u2192 discover \\u2192 curate \\u2192 train \\u2192 simulate. KPI targets: issue-to-triage <1 hr, data-to-retrain <24 hrs. Platform agnostic to data source, manages varying sensor configs.\\n    \\u25e6 Pipeline \\u2014 Reference pipeline includes auto data QC checks, frame generation (time-sync cameras\\/LiDAR\\/radar), object + map autolabeling, scene tagging per OD taxonomy. Typical ingestion-to-ready: 2\\u20133 hrs; simpler pipelines in minutes.\\n    \\u25e6 Autolabeling \\u2014 Supports ~9 classes (vehicles, trucks, peds, bikes, motorcycles, debris, cones, traffic signs\\/lights, map elements). Customers can use Applied's model or bring their own. Pricing based on data volume + workflows, not user licenses.\\n    \\u25e6 Data curation \\u2014 Geo-curation via polygons, scene tag filters (\\\"ego makes left turn\\\"), driver annotations. Curated segment sets feed into training, LogSim, ObjectSim, ISE, or NeuralSim.\\n    \\u25e6 Event triage \\u2014 Automatic triage queues (e.g., \\\"close call with pedestrian,\\\" \\\"AB trigger\\\") calculated during metrics after upload. May interested in automating analysis context around triaged events. Has internal Vantage workflow (Vikram to map out workflow) \\n\\u2022 NeuralSim\\n    \\u25e6 Reconstruction-based simulator using 3D Gaussian Splatting from drive logs \\u2014 effectively a \\\"4D closed-loop log replay.\\\" Inputs: camera + LiDAR (radar coming soon). Not fully generative; true to original scene but limited divergence from logged data.\\n    \\u25e6 Enables closed-loop modification with novel stack behavior (e.g., ego lane change). 4th dimension (time) allows actors to move independently of ego.\\n    \\u25e6 Actors: removal is straightforward; adding new actors is WIP (harvesting from different logs, relighting). Actor behavior manipulation supported (e.g., force lane change).\\n    \\u25e6 Quality checks: similarity scores and artifact detection ensure reconstructed sensor data meets quality thresholds.\\n\\u2022 ISE (Intelligent Scenario Extraction)\\n    \\u25e6 Extracts scenarios from logs with editable agents. Customizable handoff criteria (e.g., time-to-collision threshold) defines when agent transitions from logged behavior to synthetic reactive behavior.\\n    \\u25e6 Balance needed on agent reactivity \\u2014 agents shouldn't perfectly avoid collisions or it invalidates resimulation.\\n    \\u25e6 Built for bulk scenario creation via API or automatic execution through ingestion pipeline; addresses legacy extraction limitations.\\n    \\u25e6 Observer workflow: tools exist to triage events and apply observers by type, but creating observers to test scenario intent is still manual.\\n\\u2022 Agentics (Sneak Peek) \\u2014 Applied opening core capabilities via CLIs, APIs, SDKs for agentic platforms. Enables an agent to run through entire pipeline (autolabeling, tagging, simulation) externally.\\n\\u2022 HIL (Hardware-in-the-Loop)\\n    \\u25e6 Object HIL \\u2014 Test planner, controls, full post-perception stack for race conditions, latency, determinism. Runs vehicle dynamics (CarSim) at 1000 Hz. Applied treats HIL as CI\\/CD appliance, minimizing manual staffing.\\n    \\u25e6 Sensor HIL \\u2014 \\\"Direct injection\\\" approach: FPGA emulates camera\\/LiDAR\\/radar at physical level; ECU cannot differentiate from real sensor. Supports scalable sensor HIL with many cameras, ultra-low latency, synchronized rendering.\\n    \\u25e6 Replay HIL \\u2014 Xylon quattro data logger records all sensor data (GPS, CAN, Ethernet) for real-time replay to stack PC. Common use case: gating test for on-road edge cases before release.\\n    \\u25e6 Middleware mode \\u2014 No high-fidelity logger or real-time PC needed; basic CAN card + desktop; pseudo real-time (~93\\u201394%). Sufficient for May's current priority (fixing timing\\/latency on target compute). Mike Denko heading May's HIL effort.\\n\\u2022 VehicleSim \\/ CarSim\\n    \\u25e6 Goal: replace composite model with high-fidelity CarSim models to reduce false positives at edge-case velocities. CarSim has 30-year history, acquired by Applied in 2022.\\n    \\u25e6 Products: CarSim, TruckSim, BikeSim, SuspensionSim. Generic minivan model available as starting point; customizable via hundreds of parameters (suspension kinematics, steering, tires, powertrain, payloads).\\n    \\u25e6 Integration: swap motion model in ObjectSim from composite to CarSim \\u2014 no scenario rework needed. Goal: full ADP-native editing within a few quarters.\\n    \\u25e6 May could ask Toyota for their Sienna CarSim model (Toyota is a CarSim user). Path forward: start with generic minivan, swap basic params, validate.\\n    \\u25e6 Pricing ballpark shared with <@U09NURHFZKQ|matt.wood>. $40K\\/global, $300K for 300 headless licenses ($400K list for full package). Allan (vehicle sales) to follow up on specifics.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Result 6 of 10\\nChannel: #customer-experience-analytics-external (ID: C09UE6X136X)\\nFrom: Anjali Shastry (ID: U051BM6BG3F) \\nTime: 2026-03-20 09:00:03 PDT\\nMessage_ts: 1774022403.528449\\nReply count: 3\\nPermalink: [link](https:\\/\\/grid-appliedint.enterprise.slack.com\\/archives\\/C09UE6X136X\\/p1774022403528449?thread_ts=1774022403.528449&cid=C09UE6X136X)\\nText: \\nVoC interview summary: Attila Juhasz (Bosch, Synthetic Data Team)\\n\\nTL;DR: Attila is an ADP detractor (6\\/10 NPS). The Synthetic Datasets + Sensor Sim + Map Toolset combo is theoretically the most complete offering on the market, but repeated stability issues and a release process that doesn't match the documentation are eroding confidence. \\\"Sometimes we get the feeling that it is a POC-style feature especially when we want to use it at higher scale.\\\"\\n\\n:dart: Overall theme &amp; opportunity\\n\\u2022 Release quality and stability: \\\"Release process is concerning and recently there were major stability issues.\\\" Release notes often don't match documentation, and features that should work don't always. \\\"Features are not guaranteed to work.\\\"\\n\\u2022 Camera \\/ Cubemap fundamental issues: A fundamental bug in Cubemap mode for fisheye cameras is blocking their use case entirely. \\\"There are fundamental problems with Cubemap implementation, blocking my own ambition.\\\"\\n\\u2022 Documentation consistency: \\\"Release notes are not good, we rarely find the features that we are missing. Some release content is not in line with documentation.\\\"\\n\\u2022 Tagging: <@U07AJU2AZAQ|Praetzel> <@U0A0HEE0X8S|Keen> <@U051BM6BG3F|AnjaliS> \\n\\n:synthetic-datasets2: \\\"Most positive feeling\\\": Synthetic Datasets (5\\/7)\\n\\u2022 What's working: \\\"ADP Sensor Sim is the most complete package. Most easy to generate data.\\\" The combined GUI + YAML editor is strong. Web interface is intuitive, and doc search engine works well. All ground truth labels and modalities available.\\n\\u2022 Opportunities for improvement:\\n    \\u25e6 Stability: Major issues with recent releases, including a broken map import\\/ODR conversion feature.\\n    \\u25e6 Copilot: \\\"Does not always work.\\\"\\n    \\u25e6 Release notes: Often out of sync with actual product state.\\n\\u2022 Tagging: <@U08BM907RUL|Thang>\\n\\n:sensorsim: \\\"Product that needs more love\\\": Sensor Sim (5\\/7)\\n\\u2022 What's working: Combined GUI + YAML editor. Capable for standard sensor configurations.\\n\\u2022 Opportunities for improvement:\\n    \\u25e6 Cubemap mode: Fundamental implementation problems blocking fisheye camera use cases. \\\"There are fundamental problems with Cubemap implementation.\\\"\\n    \\u25e6 Camera completeness: \\\"For cameras we are using all cameras, e.g. fisheye cameras and need Cubemap modes.\\\"\\n\\u2022 Tagging: <@U0A0HEE0X8S|Keen>\\n\\nSupport &amp; Enablement Experience\\n\\u2022 Integration support (7\\/7): \\\"Applied helped to get up to speed with product.\\\" Smooth for their relatively lightweight integration.\\n\\u2022 Day-to-Day support (5\\/7): \\\"Daily office hours are super helpful.\\\" Uses docs regularly and some dedicated eng sessions.\\n\\u2022 Documentation (6\\/7): \\\"Everything that is documented is expected to work fine in the product.\\\" Good quality when current.\\n\\u2022 Feature discovery (6\\/7): \\\"You often have to search for it in the documentation... can only find it if I know what I am looking for. Copilot does not find features in documentation sometimes.\\\"\\n\\u2022 Tagging: <@U051BM6BG3F|AnjaliS> cc <@U09813WGTLN|Luca> \\n\\nSee the interview notes <https:\\/\\/docs.google.com\\/spreadsheets\\/d\\/1bNsYbzCnYTBKfzZBg7IEZw4xAXSHoqWR6QvYgeg2RwY\\/edit?gid=1601341889#gid=1601341889&range=C22|here>.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Result 7 of 10\\nChannel: #team-app-eng-pm (ID: C02J2MJ3W00)\\nFrom: Noam Rand (ID: U07QDE85QBY) \\nTime: 2025-10-08 06:07:15 PDT\\nMessage_ts: 1759928835.837959\\nPermalink: [link](https:\\/\\/grid-appliedint.enterprise.slack.com\\/archives\\/C02J2MJ3W00\\/p1759928835837959?thread_ts=1759773911.378289&cid=C02J2MJ3W00)\\nText: \\nTo comment on internal use and the role in our data engine,\\n\\u2022 2 stage &amp; 1 stage E2E: auto-sampling not in use and not in sight since we're not running any synthetic sims, only log replay. Where it maybe could be used is when the programs leans more towards validation and therefore parameter coverage could become a focus, that being said the natural direction would always be towards collecting more diverse real data and mining for these scenarios. \\n    \\u25e6 For E2E, general trend for \\\"densifying\\\" parameter space from logs is moving towards ML Sim agents rather than rules-based behaviors that are parameterized. Auto-sampling could potentially be beneficial for efficiency of the sim agent scenarios but I doubt it will look anything like auto-sampling in ADP today. <@U08BM907RUL|Thang> thoughts?\\n\\u2022 Trucking: not sure <@U034JPWUNSD|AdiV> would know. Are you guys using auto-sampling in ADP?\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Result 8 of 10\\nChannel: #team-table-notes (ID: C048467ALP6)\\nFrom: Franco Pizzani Mendoza (ID: U014M6TJDMG) \\nTime: 2025-12-05 14:48:45 PST\\nMessage_ts: 1764974925.943129\\nPermalink: [link](https:\\/\\/grid-appliedint.enterprise.slack.com\\/archives\\/C048467ALP6\\/p1764974925943129?thread_ts=1764974429.380819&cid=C048467ALP6)\\nText: \\nAttendees: <@U07FYCVHNSF|Kelso> <@UJYFKLUFJ|Freek> <@U09KWP7QQAZ|Gautham> <@U014M6TJDMG|Franco>\\n\\nNotes:\\n\\u2022 BOO\\n    \\u25e6 Scores\\n        \\u25aa\\ufe0e TL and EM meetings done\\n        \\u25aa\\ufe0e Posting improvement plans to Slack and Anaheim is 50% done, deadline is 12\\/8\\n    \\u25e6 Future rotations\\n        \\u25aa\\ufe0e Has been very valuable but less common lately at Applied\\n        \\u25aa\\ufe0e There is an effort to spin up more of an engineering team in Munich which might yield more rotation opportunities\\n    \\u25e6 Data Engine \\/ \\u201cADP 2.0\\u201d update\\n        \\u25aa\\ufe0e Feedback: Other teams may feel left behind with this naming\\n            \\u2022 It's better to think of this as a reframing, not a depreciation of original ADP\\n        \\u25aa\\ufe0e See Data Engine section below\\n\\n\\u2022 1.66 dev\\n    \\u25e6 Work is on track across the board, see Jira for latest\\n\\n\\u2022 Sprint 2025.51 planning\\n    \\u25e6 Kat will be OOO\\n    \\u25e6 Many folks taking long weekends during the holidays\\n    \\u25e6 Eng day expectations for sprint planning will be adjusted down\\n    \\u25e6 If you\\u2019re planning on being OOO part of holidays please file Rippling requests before the switch to Workday next week\\n\\n\\u2022 Stack support\\n    \\u25e6 Synthetic datasets\\n        \\u25aa\\ufe0e SF map progress\\n            \\u2022 SF crops still too bulky for sensor sim\\n            \\u2022 Created 1 single smaller SF crop that seems to work\\n            \\u2022 Problems running residential preset\\n                \\u25e6 Initially windows related, but also hit memory issues\\n                \\u25e6 Work with Patrick to iron out the memory issues\\n                \\u25e6 Freek should keep Patrick\\u2019s Linux desktop on return next week\\n        \\u25aa\\ufe0e OSM stats\\n            \\u2022 This is running behind schedule, Kelso will focus on it Monday 12\\/8\\n            \\u2022 Want metrics for estimated trajectories based on map size\\n            \\u2022 Formula for expected output based on number of trajectories\\n            \\u2022 SDS trying to do the same for drive logs\\n            \\u2022 This should become a platform solution (data engine)\\n    \\u25e6 SLAM labeling\\n        \\u25aa\\ufe0e Moved from google docs to Jira to track work with workflows\\n            \\u2022 Let\\u2019s apply the new Slack > Jira workflow and auto child tasks\\n        \\u25aa\\ufe0e MTV v2.3 intersection labeling wrapping up early next week\\n        \\u25aa\\ufe0e SF v2.3 next\\n        \\u25aa\\ufe0e Telus onboarding\\n        \\u25aa\\ufe0e Tools All Hands workflow overview and impact recap on 12\\/10\\n    \\u25e6 HD map labeling\\n        \\u25aa\\ufe0e Ann arbor map had some issues, need better point cloud support\\n            \\u2022 Base map and point cloud are at different heights\\n    \\u25e6 Trucks\\n        \\u25aa\\ufe0e Scheduled open loop test\\n        \\u25aa\\ufe0e Maps are driven daily and need to be updated to be accurate\\n\\n\\u2022 Customers\\n    \\u25e6 Komatsu Mining team engagement\\n        \\u25aa\\ufe0e Want to generate underground maps: <https:\\/\\/applied-tools.slack.com\\/archives\\/CKK69UYP8\\/p1764780040073419|context here>\\n            \\u2022 We have done this before\\n            \\u2022 Relatively low effort with the right inputs, but very custom\\/specific work\\n    \\u25e6 Honda data engine maps\\n        \\u25aa\\ufe0e <@U07A04MH59N|Maximus> will support using GPS pose from drive log or OSM\\n        \\u25aa\\ufe0e Slack <https:\\/\\/applied-tools.slack.com\\/archives\\/C09PZHXQA69\\/p1764812704583569|thread>\\n\\n\\u2022 Data Engine update\\n    \\u25e6 \\u201cADP 2.0\\u201d product architecture\\n        \\u25aa\\ufe0e CLI-first platform \\u2013 API first product\\n            \\u2022 Core content library (including maps and scenarios)\\n            \\u2022 Job manager (single and bulk)\\n            \\u2022 Insights (results)\\n            \\u2022 Goal is to decouple the API from the frontend, making it  more modular, and also enable for Cursor-like AI interfaces.\\n        \\u25aa\\ufe0e World modeling\\n            \\u2022 Scenario extraction\\n            \\u2022 Map extraction and editing\\n            \\u2022 World reconstruction and generation\\n            \\u2022 Sensor config and validation\\n        \\u25aa\\ufe0e Sim &amp; Eval\\n        \\u25aa\\ufe0e V&amp;V - safety case\\n    \\u25e6 Started to create roadmap for each existing ADP product\\n        \\u25aa\\ufe0e Goal: Reduce churn of needing various complicated product licenses instead focus on workflows (and licensing revenue by workflow tokens)\\n        \\u25aa\\ufe0e Product capabilities tied to workflows\\n        \\u25aa\\ufe0e Akshat will setup meetings with each team to review the product capabilities and stack rank which we should, expect week of 12\\/8\\n        \\u25aa\\ufe0e Roadmaps for each product due by early January\\n        \\u25aa\\ufe0e Examples:\\n            \\u2022 Map extraction \\/ editing\\n            \\u2022 World Generation\\n        \\u25aa\\ufe0e Feedback:\\n            \\u2022 There are many product engineering constraints today\\n            \\u2022 Reducing friction by not jumping between products sounds great!\\n            \\u2022 Past pain related to Unreal. One issue is the latency between all the different microservices. To contrast: Carla has things more integrated all in Unreal instead of 50\\/50.\\n                \\u25e6 One request from PeterL is to come up with 4-5 workflows and strict API contracts (including timing)\\n            \\u2022 Comfy UI is good inspiration\\n    \\u25e6 Traditional ADP products will continue to exist\\n        \\u25aa\\ufe0e But pushing to a workflow model that wraps those products without the customer necessarily knowing \\/ needing to be inside those products\\n\\n\\u2022 Longer term roadmap\\n    \\u25e6 Scheduling Worlds planning sessions in January\\n    \\u25e6 Scheduling Worlds onsite to Sunnyvale HQ\\n        \\u25aa\\ufe0e Should include PaulP and Jansen\\n        \\u25aa\\ufe0e More February to early March, align folks schedules now\\n    \\u25e6 Large worlds plant review recap\\n        \\u25aa\\ufe0e <@UJYFKLUFJ|Freek> and <@U07FYCVHNSF|Kelso> to roadmap this out in 2025.51\\n\\n\\u2022 Tools code yellow\\n    \\u25e6 Automated testing for Map Toolset\\n        \\u25aa\\ufe0e 2025.51 work for everyone but product eng work trends this to :large_yellow_circle: and at risk of slipping to 2026.01\\n    \\u25e6 Automated maps platform service integration tests and health checks\\n        \\u25aa\\ufe0e Ben created Jira <https:\\/\\/appliedintuition.atlassian.net\\/jira\\/software\\/c\\/projects\\/ATDEV\\/list?filter=type%20%3D%20%22Epic%22%20AND%20assignee%20%3D%20%22712020%3Af5774615-584e-4d8d-ba9d-b4ce43ccf3fe%22&selectedIssue=ATDEV-15740|epic> and subtasks, will add to overall tracking spreadsheet\\n        \\u25aa\\ufe0e Tasks need to be allocated to ICs and scheduled for 2025.51 or 2026.01\\n\\n\\u2022 Recruiting\\n    \\u25e6 Mapping Specialists\\n        \\u25aa\\ufe0e JoshuaL started 12\\/2\\n        \\u25aa\\ufe0e ChrisP starts 12\\/8\\n        \\u25aa\\ufe0e Alejandro Aguilar - responded via LinkedIn, Kelso will schedule IPS\\n    \\u25e6 Offers stage\\n        \\u25aa\\ufe0e Aaron Chan (MT) other offer from Snapchat\\n        \\u25aa\\ufe0e Spencer Ferguson (MP)\\n    \\u25e6 Upcoming onsites\\n        \\u25aa\\ufe0e 12\\/9 - Ruimin Zeng (Bytedance, TuSimple maps)\\n        \\u25aa\\ufe0e 12\\/9 - Allen Cao (Amazon, UC Berkeley)\\n        \\u25aa\\ufe0e 12\\/15 Joshua Peng (Fortinet, Salesforce) (MP)\\n        \\u25aa\\ufe0e 12\\/17 Xiaohan Yu (Samsara, Cornell)\\n        \\u25aa\\ufe0e Then Xmas and NYE weeks, and things will pick up in January\\n    \\u25e6 Recruiting weather report\\n        \\u25aa\\ufe0e New grad season closed by early November\\n        \\u25aa\\ufe0e New grad onsite fair in Q1 with team matching \\u2013 goal is to reduce attrition, create FOMO at eng schools\\n        \\u25aa\\ufe0e Applied recruiting momentum generally slowed in November and December across Tools (result of hiring \\u201cpause\\u201d)\\n        \\u25aa\\ufe0e Pipeline is reactivated and with more GenSWE roles open and coming onsite\\n        \\u25aa\\ufe0e January and February always see burst of inbound and activity\\n\\nAction items:\\n\\u2022 <@U04MJNQ4MT6|Ryan Tarr (OOO sabbatical until 6\\/29)> and <@U07FYCVHNSF|Kelso> to post TL and EM improvement plans by Monday 12\\/8\\n\\u2022 <@UJYFKLUFJ|Freek> to finalize Jira ticket automation workflow for Worlds team week of 12\\/8 cc <@U06RNEW5RH6|Akshat>\\n\\u2022 <@UJYFKLUFJ|Freek> and <@U07FYCVHNSF|Kelso> to roadmap large worlds eng work in 2025.51\\n\\u2022 <@U07FYCVHNSF|Kelso> and <@U05USCERQ3W|Jonathan> shadow Telus to learn about their workflow in January\\n\\u2022 <@U014M6TJDMG|Franco> to poll Worlds + <@U06243QPPBL|PaulP> + <@U023G2ABKSS|Jansen> about Sunnyvale HQ onsite timing for Feb\\/March\\n\\u2022 <@U09KWP7QQAZ|Gautham> to followup with Kelso about Map Stats as a service for Data Engine\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Result 9 of 10\\nChannel: #eng-synthetic-data (ID: C09FVL7CXB6)\\nFrom: Sergio Perez (ID: U06T9L3GB5F) \\nTime: 2026-05-18 14:11:18 PDT\\nMessage_ts: 1779138678.848939\\nPermalink: [link](https:\\/\\/grid-appliedint.enterprise.slack.com\\/archives\\/C09FVL7CXB6\\/p1779138678848939?thread_ts=1779138283.633169&cid=C09FVL7CXB6)\\nText: \\nContext: <https:\\/\\/appliedintuition.atlassian.net\\/browse\\/ATDEV-32223|ATDEV-32223>\\n\\n<@U07AY0G968H|Andrew McGovern> is showing Synthetic Datasets workflow in a workshop for Komatsu using ADP 1.70. This will show the existing Dataset Generator SDK and the new storage\\/export flow enable_synthetic_datasets_storage: true\\n\\nMaster branch contains many recent latest changes to support lidar exports, more polished UI (export progress, dataset visualizing, etc):\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Result 10 of 10\\nChannel: #product-data-engine (ID: C0537MKT25T)\\nFrom: Pedro Judice (ID: U03SGJ8K6J1) \\nTime: 2026-04-28 18:19:38 PDT\\nMessage_ts: 1777425578.549989\\nPermalink: [link](https:\\/\\/grid-appliedint.enterprise.slack.com\\/archives\\/C0537MKT25T\\/p1777425578549989?thread_ts=1777425171.016569&cid=C0537MKT25T)\\nText: \\nHi, sharing here the latest on how to ship and download the Data Engine SDK for external customers. Please refer to <https:\\/\\/appliedintuition.atlassian.net\\/wiki\\/x\\/UgK9nw|Data Engine SDK \\u2014 Shipping, Testing &amp; Releasing>\\n\\nA few new things:\\n\\u2022 We are now packaging the SDK and making it available for download under: <https:\\/\\/home.applied.co\\/downloads\\/>\\n\\u2022 You can trigger a BK pipeline to release the latest version (or from any branch) using the command line from applied3 docker: adp ship_data_engine_sdk\\n    \\u25e6 <https:\\/\\/buildkite.com\\/applied-intuition\\/data-engine-sdk-release-dev|Staging Pipeline> -> <https:\\/\\/home.staging.applied.co\\/downloads>\\n    \\u25e6 <https:\\/\\/buildkite.com\\/applied-intuition\\/data-engine-sdk-release-dev|Prod Pipeline> -> <https:\\/\\/home.applied.co\\/downloads\\/>\\n\\u2022 To release to production, you can trigger with adp ship_data_engine_sdk --prod --customer <> \\n\\nTo download, you can click on \\\"Download Beta for Linux\\\" and select the Data Engine SDK under ADP Ship\\n\\n---\\n\\n\",\"pagination_info\":\"For the next page of results use cursor `Q1VSUkVOVF9QQUdFOjI=`\\n\"}"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01AeQvEvhszVJhWytvQBSm5n","session_id":"e608aebc-1e8f-4a54-bfcc-c9052cb98c4e","uuid":"00cc4fcb-68e3-466d-a0f3-b62947ebd9e9","timestamp":"2026-06-01T17:05:27.883Z","subagent_type":"general-purpose","task_description":"Research ROSbag/MCAP format for ADP pipeline"}
