{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Fv43rLaR9d9y8uWwhTEUha","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\"results\":\"# Search Results for: conversion script ADP ROSbag katana synthetic\\n\\n## Messages (10 results)\\n### Result 1 of 10\\nChannel: #ext-program-katana-toolchain (ID: C09LSNE9Q0Y)\\nFrom: Andrew McGovern (ID: U07AY0G968H) \\nTime: 2026-06-01 09:22:31 PDT\\nMessage_ts: 1780330951.672899\\nPermalink: [link](https:\\/\\/grid-appliedint.enterprise.slack.com\\/archives\\/C09LSNE9Q0Y\\/p1780330951672899?thread_ts=1780322410.292029&cid=C09LSNE9Q0Y)\\nText: \\nDiscussed live, notes from conversation here:\\n\\u2022 Data Engine pipeline still being built on on Applied side\\n\\u2022 Eventually, this ADP data will need to be written to a ROS bag. These message definitions are not yet set in stone. Once they are, we can begin converting this ADP data into ROS bag\\n\\u2022 For now, team will focus on:\\n    \\u25e6 1. Committing scripts into the vehicle-os-katana repo at \\/katana\\/katana_adp in a new folder\\n    \\u25e6 2. Generating datasets with occlusions and weather \\n\\n---\\n\\n### Result 2 of 10\\nChannel: #program-komatsu-surround-view-system (ID: C08K6CTGCDS)\\nFrom: Alex Del Re (ID: U063Y6FQA5V) \\nTime: 2026-05-06 15:32:11 PDT\\nMessage_ts: 1778106731.106039\\nPermalink: [link](https:\\/\\/grid-appliedint.enterprise.slack.com\\/archives\\/C08K6CTGCDS\\/p1778106731106039?thread_ts=1778091961.072579&cid=C08K6CTGCDS)\\nText: \\nopened a PR and have it up for review <https:\\/\\/applied-tools.slack.com\\/archives\\/C09HK34LPHQ\\/p1778106708623479|here>\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Result 3 of 10\\nChannel: #eng-pmt (ID: C07NE8HF3JP)\\nFrom: Ashli Forbes (ID: U09AUE77ZU5) \\nTime: 2026-05-27 17:03:00 PDT\\nMessage_ts: 1779926580.390859\\nPermalink: [link](https:\\/\\/grid-appliedint.enterprise.slack.com\\/archives\\/C07NE8HF3JP\\/p1779926580390859?thread_ts=1779925974.861829&cid=C07NE8HF3JP)\\nText: \\ni have just merged the generic one on katana repo\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Result 4 of 10\\nChannel: DM (ID: D0651MWAD4Y)\\nParticipants: Alex Del Re (ID: U063Y6FQA5V), Alex Del Re (ID: U063Y6FQA5V)\\nFrom: Alex Del Re (ID: U063Y6FQA5V) \\nTime: 2026-05-18 11:09:12 PDT\\nMessage_ts: 1779127752.401599\\nPermalink: [link](https:\\/\\/grid-appliedint.enterprise.slack.com\\/archives\\/D0651MWAD4Y\\/p1779127752401599?thread_ts=1779127712.967979&cid=D0651MWAD4Y)\\nText: \\n:thread:05\\/18\\/2026: [Katana <> Applied] Virtual Toolchain Office Hours\\nKomatsu Attendees: Aravind Pandian, Sam Manickam, Fan Lou, Urara Kono, Vibhav Adivi, Matthew Sullivan, Wes Taylor, Brian White, Jacquelyn Nagel, Mark Ruzicka, Nathan Mueller, Robert Florich, Brian Mooyoung Lee, Tyler Gibson, Saketh Garuda\\nApplied Attendees: <@U07AY0G968H|Andrew McGovern>\\n<https:\\/\\/docs.google.com\\/document\\/d\\/1-qsinB4xM_M-64fdkLkfwInbQDQO6-2BkwlfiCZyh3k\\/edit?usp=drive_web&tab=t.rj301gipv0gm|Gemini notes>\\nDiscussion:\\n\\u2022 Workshop logistics finalized for Synthetic Data Sets Workshop (Wed May 20, 10am Central); scripts shared via Drive\\/email for those without vehicle_os_katana repo access\\n\\u2022 Sensor validation scoped to fog + dust only; PoD vs mean optical range defined as primary KPI; rain model excluded as it contradicts FKA data\\n\\u2022 FKA data parsing identified as critical path: Komatsu team parses Azure FKA data; Andrew handles ADP simulation scenarios and merges into shared repo\\n\\u2022 ADP 170.35 deploys to katana.apply.dev Wednesday ~6pm Central (~2hr downtime); cloud engine errors pending Slack debug\\nAction items:\\n\\u2022 <@U07AY0G968H|Andrew McGovern>: Create fog and dust ADP simulation scenarios, upload to vehicle_os_katana repo\\n\\u2022 Jacquelyn Nagel: Parse FKA data to extract PoD over mean optical range (also Mark Ruzicka, Tyler Gibson)\\n\\u2022 Jacquelyn Nagel: Share current dust simulation files with Andrew McGovern\\n\\u2022 <@U07AY0G968H|Andrew McGovern>: Send workshop scripts to Komatsu team via Drive\\/email before Wednesday\\n\\u2022 <@U07AY0G968H|Andrew McGovern>: Verify which YOLO version is used by Komatsu stack team\\n\\u2022 <@U07AY0G968H|Andrew McGovern>: Configure rain lens YAML field for camera rain simulation\\n\\u2022 <@U07AY0G968H|Andrew McGovern>: Evaluate rain simulation feasibility before end of June release\\n\\u2022 Vibhav Adivi: Share cloud engine error screenshots via Slack for debugging\\n\\u2022 Jacquelyn Nagel: Verify FKA data source (Komatsu team or external)\\n\\u2022 Jacquelyn Nagel: Request ADP access for Gabriella via Applied IT\\n\\u2022 <@U063Y6FQA5V|AlexD>: Create dedicated Slack channel for Komatsu-to-Applied-IT communication\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Result 5 of 10\\nChannel: #eng-vehicle-os-hmi (ID: C067A9VMFTJ)\\nFrom: Vidyut Basrurkar (ID: U01CFSSHH7U) \\nTime: 2026-05-22 14:51:25 PDT\\nMessage_ts: 1779486685.785569\\nPermalink: [link](https:\\/\\/grid-appliedint.enterprise.slack.com\\/archives\\/C067A9VMFTJ\\/p1779486685785569?thread_ts=1779401810.541689&cid=C067A9VMFTJ)\\nText: \\nWill this help me get vehicle-os-katana setup properly? I will need to setup another katana variant so I can have an katana_8295_adaptive variant I can build from the vehicle-os-katana repo\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Result 6 of 10\\nChannel: DM (ID: D0651MWAD4Y)\\nParticipants: Alex Del Re (ID: U063Y6FQA5V), Alex Del Re (ID: U063Y6FQA5V)\\nFrom: Alex Del Re (ID: U063Y6FQA5V) \\nTime: 2026-05-27 16:07:38 PDT\\nMessage_ts: 1779923258.139899\\nPermalink: [link](https:\\/\\/grid-appliedint.enterprise.slack.com\\/archives\\/D0651MWAD4Y\\/p1779923258139899?thread_ts=1779912498.654339&cid=D0651MWAD4Y)\\nText: \\n:thread:05\\/27\\/2026: Katana synthetic scenario &amp; ML workflow\\nKomatsu Attendees: Brian White\\nApplied Attendees: <@U056B308XB2|Ting>, <@U07AY0G968H|Andrew McGovern>, <@U091N2DPLJH|SaiR>\\n<https:\\/\\/docs.google.com\\/document\\/d\\/1Dg-kCztuSURWwZsMJNWzc7W1ucNt6hcDWWgnZ2IluDA\\/edit?usp=drive_web&tab=t.xtc51ba0xurs|Gemini notes>\\nDiscussion:\\n\\u2022 3D perception model (replacing YOLO 2D prototype) targeted for mine_assist stack merge by end of June 2026, aligned with Komatsu release cadence\\n\\u2022 Synthetic data via ADP\\/sensor sim confirmed as SVS training supplement; Lance format already supported by MLRL pipeline, 10k labeled frames ready from sensor sim team\\n\\u2022 Training requires 16-32 A100s via Lilypad cluster orchestration; unclear if Lilypad can be exposed to Komatsu - needs ML infra assessment\\n\\u2022 Co-development scope (who owns model training vs. Komatsu independence) remains undefined; account team alignment needed with Jeff Moran and Mike Rick\\nAction items:\\n\\u2022 <@U056B308XB2|Ting>: Clarify SVS co-development scope with Jeff Moran and Mike Rick on training responsibilities\\n\\u2022 <@U056B308XB2|Ting>: Start thread to identify MLRL Bazel targets needed for vehicle-os-katana release to enable Komatsu training\\n\\u2022 <@U091N2DPLJH|SaiR>: DM Andrew McGovern with Chunu\\/David contact info for Lance export pipeline\\n\\u2022 <@U07AY0G968H|Andrew McGovern>: Coordinate with Chunu's sensor sim team on ADP-to-Lance export for SVS distorted cameras\\n\\u2022 <@U07AY0G968H|Andrew McGovern>: Evaluate promoting ADP-to-Lance conversion to a standard product export option\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Result 7 of 10\\nChannel: #inc-260316-workbench-missing-from-katana-cluster (ID: C0AMTLJE2EL)\\nFrom: Andrew McGovern (ID: U07AY0G968H) \\nTime: 2026-03-17 17:49:36 PDT\\nMessage_ts: 1773794976.599349\\nPermalink: [link](https:\\/\\/grid-appliedint.enterprise.slack.com\\/archives\\/C0AMTLJE2EL\\/p1773794976599349?thread_ts=1773783946.704749&cid=C0AMTLJE2EL)\\nText: \\nThis looks like a problem, katana uses both of these\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Result 8 of 10\\nChannel: #code-reviews-core-stack (ID: C061LKB7JH4)\\nFrom: Ryan Tanary (ID: U0881NRLWMC) \\nTime: 2026-04-29 12:02:56 PDT\\nMessage_ts: 1777489376.552979\\nReply count: 1\\nPermalink: [link](https:\\/\\/grid-appliedint.enterprise.slack.com\\/archives\\/C061LKB7JH4\\/p1777489376552979?thread_ts=1777489376.552979&cid=C061LKB7JH4)\\nText: \\n<@U063Y6FQA5V|AlexD> <https:\\/\\/github.com\\/ExtAppliedVehicleOS\\/vehicle-os-katana\\/pull\\/314|Updated Katana example applications to use user-friendly middleware>\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Result 9 of 10\\nChannel: DM (ID: D0651MWAD4Y)\\nParticipants: Alex Del Re (ID: U063Y6FQA5V), Alex Del Re (ID: U063Y6FQA5V)\\nFrom: Alex Del Re (ID: U063Y6FQA5V) \\nTime: 2026-05-28 14:08:14 PDT\\nMessage_ts: 1780002494.574089\\nPermalink: [link](https:\\/\\/grid-appliedint.enterprise.slack.com\\/archives\\/D0651MWAD4Y\\/p1780002494574089?thread_ts=1779991792.234049&cid=D0651MWAD4Y)\\nText: \\n:thread:05\\/28\\/2026: Toolchain Weekly Sync\\nKomatsu Attendees: Brian White\\nApplied Attendees: <@U07AY0G968H|Andrew McGovern>\\n<https:\\/\\/docs.google.com\\/document\\/d\\/1u6vF4xgNlsu2n9U0r5ygqUcIHfPE_zO1p-FWtFBg6uQ\\/edit?usp=drive_web&tab=t.uxknwb8ro5un|Gemini notes>\\nDiscussion:\\n\\u2022 Model pipeline: transitioning from 2D (YOLO) to custom 3D bounding box model; training pipeline delayed to next release; data engine conversion script ready to migrate to VOS Katana\\n\\u2022 Sensor validation: ADP simulator fog modeling uses deterministic 0\\/100% transitions (unacceptable); custom LiDAR plugin being built for gradual probability-of-detection transitions (ETA next week)\\n\\u2022 FKA data anomaly: \\\"swoop\\\" in PoD curves for 10%\\/80% targets traced to cluster-based SAE J471 KPI1 averaging methodology; raw frame data from FKA needed to confirm\\n\\u2022 Team continuity: Andrew and Timothy covering daily virtual toolchain tasks during Alex's July honeymoon\\nAction items:\\n\\u2022 <@U07AY0G968H|Andrew McGovern>: Develop custom LiDAR plugin for gradual probability-of-detection transitions\\n\\u2022 <@U07AY0G968H|Andrew McGovern>: Migrate data engine conversion script to Vehicle OS Katana repo\\n\\u2022 Brian White: Contact FKA via Sunny Patel to investigate PoD data anomaly\\n\\u2022 <@U07AY0G968H|Andrew McGovern>: Notify Jacqueline about plugin capabilities and confirm AWS ECR access before delivery\\n\\u2022 <@U07AY0G968H|Andrew McGovern>: Transfer project context to Andrew and Timothy before Alex absence\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Result 10 of 10\\nChannel: #code-reviews-dev-tooling (ID: C09HK34LPHQ)\\nFrom: Alex Del Re (ID: U063Y6FQA5V) \\nTime: 2026-05-06 15:31:48 PDT\\nMessage_ts: 1778106708.623479\\nReply count: 1\\nPermalink: [link](https:\\/\\/grid-appliedint.enterprise.slack.com\\/archives\\/C09HK34LPHQ\\/p1778106708623479?thread_ts=1778106708.623479&cid=C09HK34LPHQ)\\nText: \\n<https:\\/\\/github.com\\/AppliedNeuron\\/core-stack\\/pull\\/82907|NEU-44739: Add katana to upstream change pipeline workflow> <@U09DVKBSKMZ|Sohum> <@U05LH20HF0V|JasmineW>\\n\\n---\\n\\n\",\"pagination_info\":\"For the next page of results use cursor `Q1VSUkVOVF9QQUdFOjI=`\\n\"}"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01AeQvEvhszVJhWytvQBSm5n","session_id":"e608aebc-1e8f-4a54-bfcc-c9052cb98c4e","uuid":"a156e4c3-4a54-45af-a617-40b9ce2c83eb","timestamp":"2026-06-01T17:05:36.531Z","subagent_type":"general-purpose","task_description":"Research ROSbag/MCAP format for ADP pipeline"}
