{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Tb8AN1apnrVsjjw1sXYkAQ","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\"messages\":\"=== THREAD PARENT MESSAGE ===\\nFrom: Office Hours Agenda (B0A4WHKRL4B)\\nTime: 2026-06-01 07:00:10 PDT\\nMessage TS: 1780322410.292029\\n:mega: Office Hours is happening 11 am CT today (June 1, 2026) Please thread any topics you would like to discuss\\n\\n=== THREAD REPLIES (2 total) ===\\n\\n--- Reply 1 of 2 ---\\nFrom: Brian Mooyoung Lee (U09930W4A3H)\\nTime: 2026-06-01 08:26:19 PDT\\nMessage TS: 1780327579.345119\\n<@U07AY0G968H|Andrew McGovern>\\n\\nI would like to understand the Applied workflow after generating synthetic scenarios and datasets. Specifically, what should be done with the scenario outputs? Are there recommended best practices for reusing or sharing scenarios, or for incorporating them into model validation activities?\\n\\n--- Reply 2 of 2 ---\\nFrom: Andrew McGovern (U07AY0G968H)\\nTime: 2026-06-01 09:22:31 PDT\\nMessage TS: 1780330951.672899\\nDiscussed live, notes from conversation here:\\n\\u2022 Data Engine pipeline still being built on on Applied side\\n\\u2022 Eventually, this ADP data will need to be written to a ROS bag. These message definitions are not yet set in stone. Once they are, we can begin converting this ADP data into ROS bag\\n\\u2022 For now, team will focus on:\\n    \\u25e6 1. Committing scripts into the `vehicle-os-katana` repo at `\\/katana\\/katana_adp` in a new folder\\n    \\u25e6 2. Generating datasets with occlusions and weather \\n\",\"pagination_info\":\"There are no more messages in this thread.\\n\"}"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01AeQvEvhszVJhWytvQBSm5n","session_id":"e608aebc-1e8f-4a54-bfcc-c9052cb98c4e","uuid":"38fb0b37-4b62-41a5-a36f-cd8eb88ab03b","timestamp":"2026-06-01T17:05:41.954Z","subagent_type":"general-purpose","task_description":"Research ROSbag/MCAP format for ADP pipeline"}
