{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DY8vgEqFMAj6BMZdjqwC25","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\"results\":\"# Search Results for: Lance format ADP synthetic data SVS perception training pipeline\\n\\n## Messages (10 results)\\n### Result 1 of 10\\nChannel: DM (ID: D0651MWAD4Y)\\nParticipants: Alex Del Re (ID: U063Y6FQA5V), Alex Del Re (ID: U063Y6FQA5V)\\nFrom: Alex Del Re (ID: U063Y6FQA5V) \\nTime: 2026-05-27 16:07:38 PDT\\nMessage_ts: 1779923258.139899\\nPermalink: [link](https:\\/\\/grid-appliedint.enterprise.slack.com\\/archives\\/D0651MWAD4Y\\/p1779923258139899?thread_ts=1779912498.654339&cid=D0651MWAD4Y)\\nText: \\n:thread:05\\/27\\/2026: Katana synthetic scenario &amp; ML workflow\\nKomatsu Attendees: Brian White\\nApplied Attendees: <@U056B308XB2|Ting>, <@U07AY0G968H|Andrew McGovern>, <@U091N2DPLJH|SaiR>\\n<https:\\/\\/docs.google.com\\/document\\/d\\/1Dg-kCztuSURWwZsMJNWzc7W1ucNt6hcDWWgnZ2IluDA\\/edit?usp=drive_web&tab=t.xtc51ba0xurs|Gemini notes>\\nDiscussion:\\n\\u2022 3D perception model (replacing YOLO 2D prototype) targeted for mine_assist stack merge by end of June 2026, aligned with Komatsu release cadence\\n\\u2022 Synthetic data via ADP\\/sensor sim confirmed as SVS training supplement; Lance format already supported by MLRL pipeline, 10k labeled frames ready from sensor sim team\\n\\u2022 Training requires 16-32 A100s via Lilypad cluster orchestration; unclear if Lilypad can be exposed to Komatsu - needs ML infra assessment\\n\\u2022 Co-development scope (who owns model training vs. Komatsu independence) remains undefined; account team alignment needed with Jeff Moran and Mike Rick\\nAction items:\\n\\u2022 <@U056B308XB2|Ting>: Clarify SVS co-development scope with Jeff Moran and Mike Rick on training responsibilities\\n\\u2022 <@U056B308XB2|Ting>: Start thread to identify MLRL Bazel targets needed for vehicle-os-katana release to enable Komatsu training\\n\\u2022 <@U091N2DPLJH|SaiR>: DM Andrew McGovern with Chunu\\/David contact info for Lance export pipeline\\n\\u2022 <@U07AY0G968H|Andrew McGovern>: Coordinate with Chunu's sensor sim team on ADP-to-Lance export for SVS distorted cameras\\n\\u2022 <@U07AY0G968H|Andrew McGovern>: Evaluate promoting ADP-to-Lance conversion to a standard product export option\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Result 2 of 10\\nChannel: #eng-data-engine (ID: C06632KLGPM)\\nFrom: Andrew McGovern (ID: U07AY0G968H) \\nTime: 2026-05-20 10:16:59 PDT\\nMessage_ts: 1779297419.006539\\nPermalink: [link](https:\\/\\/grid-appliedint.enterprise.slack.com\\/archives\\/C06632KLGPM\\/p1779297419006539?thread_ts=1779297415.281679&cid=C06632KLGPM)\\nText: \\nKomatsu is interested in using our data engine model training pipeline. They want to do this\\n\\n1. Generate synthetic data with ADP - they already know how to do this well\\n2. Use that data to edit an existing perception model for object detection\\n3. Run the perception model on real and\\/or synthetic data\\n\\nI've been working with <@U056B308XB2|Ting> so far on this, but not sure what the model pipelines around it actually look like. What does a model training deployment for a customer look like?\\n\\ncc <@U063Y6FQA5V|AlexD>\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Result 3 of 10\\nChannel: #program-komatsu (ID: C0961E7856J)\\nFrom: Alex Del Re (ID: U063Y6FQA5V) \\nTime: 2026-05-19 08:40:21 PDT\\nMessage_ts: 1779205221.762099\\nPermalink: [link](https:\\/\\/grid-appliedint.enterprise.slack.com\\/archives\\/C0961E7856J\\/p1779205221762099?thread_ts=1779120287.921819&cid=C0961E7856J)\\nText: \\nVirtual Toolchain \\n\\u2022 :status_green: Deliver Developer Studio SIL virtualizations to enable inter-zonal testing for Autolube and Engine Interface applications\\n    \\u25e6 Hosting Peoria SIL test workshop week of 2206.21 for autolube testing\\n\\u2022 :large_yellow_circle: Integrate SVS software with ADP sensor simulations\\n    \\u25e6 Focus for SVS integration will be synthetic datasets integration into SVS training pipeline. \\n    \\u25e6 Going to discuss with <@U06EB2G5EGM|Sergey> on Data Engine pipeline options for Komatsu team this sprint\\n\\u2022 :status_green: Enhance the CI\\/CD pipeline to accelerate developer velocity, improving reliability, and enable consistent resource access\\n    \\u25e6 adding workbench CI testing based on outputs from Peoria workshop\\n    \\u25e6 going to release first proposal for katana repo release process this sprint \\n\\u2022 :status_green: Enable Machine Learning team to generate synthetic data &amp; evaluate performance change on ODS on oblique angle scenarios\\n    \\u25e6 <@U07AY0G968H|Andrew McGovern> to host SD workshop with ML team this week\\n\\u2022 :status_green: Validate synthetic sensors with Komatsu lab data to understand object detection metrics in different environmental conditions\\n    \\u25e6 <@U07AY0G968H|Andrew McGovern> reviewing with sensor validation team to discuss \\n\\u2022 :large_yellow_circle: Develop 830E TruckSim model to enable Smart AHT controls simulation testing\\n    \\u25e6 <@U0A0B3GJSJX|Jeff Moran> - Komatsu told us they are no longer interested in simulation capabilities for the 830E, but rather the 830PA. \\n\\u2022 :large_yellow_circle: \\/ :red_circle: Define plan to integrate 930E TruckSim model with steering and braking applications for SDV SW team\\n    \\u25e6 <@U0A0B3GJSJX|Jeff Moran> - seems like the direction with Katana work-streams (SDV and SDA) is to test with TruckSim models for the 830 program for controls simulations. We originally got direction from Lee to integrate a 930 model with simulation, but seems like this is not the case. I am planning to discuss with Wes, BrianW, and JoeB on the plan for working with TruckSims this week\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Result 4 of 10\\nChannel: #program-komatsu-surround-view-system (ID: C08K6CTGCDS)\\nFrom: Andrew McGovern (ID: U07AY0G968H) \\nTime: 2026-05-27 14:14:08 PDT\\nMessage_ts: 1779916448.537339\\nPermalink: [link](https:\\/\\/grid-appliedint.enterprise.slack.com\\/archives\\/C08K6CTGCDS\\/p1779916448537339?thread_ts=1779916420.875339&cid=C08K6CTGCDS)\\nText: \\nI'm working with <@U063Y6FQA5V|AlexD> and <@U056B308XB2|Ting> to scope out how Komatsu can leverage some existing Applied tooling to train a perception model. They are interested in setting up the capacity to edit an existing model on synthetic data from ADP. The core question we did not know was, \\\"who is actually responsible for training the SVS perception module?\\\". Applied has put effort into creating a model to get started, but AFAIK Komatsu will eventually need the capacity to edit this model on their own.\\n\\n<@U0A0B3GJSJX|Jeff Moran> &amp; <@U09DVKBSKMZ|Sohum>, what is the split of responsibilities here? Have we determined how the co-development of an SVS model will work?\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Result 5 of 10\\nChannel: DM (ID: D07E5HPJFM2)\\nParticipants: Alex Del Re (ID: U063Y6FQA5V), Andrew McGovern (ID: U07AY0G968H)\\nFrom: Andrew McGovern (ID: U07AY0G968H) \\nTime: 2026-05-27 09:29:15 PDT\\nMessage_ts: 1779899355.269039\\nReply count: 21\\nPermalink: [link](https:\\/\\/grid-appliedint.enterprise.slack.com\\/archives\\/D07E5HPJFM2\\/p1779899355269039?thread_ts=1779899355.269039&cid=D07E5HPJFM2)\\nText: \\nHey, hope you're feeling better today! I started <https:\\/\\/applied-home.slack.com\\/archives\\/C08K6CTGCDS\\/p1779821914224589?thread_ts=1779821907.275389&cid=C08K6CTGCDS|this thread> with SVS. I scoped it to either an ADP sensor sim integration (visualize bounding boxes), or a data engine model training pipeline.\\n\\nHonestly either of these could satisfy the requirement, Integrate SVS software with ADP sensor simulations. Have you heard from Komatsu a preference here?\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Result 6 of 10\\nChannel: #program-komatsu-surround-view-system (ID: C08K6CTGCDS)\\nFrom: Andrew McGovern (ID: U07AY0G968H) \\nTime: 2026-05-26 11:58:34 PDT\\nMessage_ts: 1779821914.224589\\nPermalink: [link](https:\\/\\/grid-appliedint.enterprise.slack.com\\/archives\\/C08K6CTGCDS\\/p1779821914224589?thread_ts=1779821907.275389&cid=C08K6CTGCDS)\\nText: \\nOne of the release goals for the Virtual Toolchain workstream is to \\\"Integrate SVS software with ADP sensor simulations\\\". Deadline is end of June.\\n\\nThe way I see it, there are two ways forward:\\n1. Open-loop Sims: Running ADP and sending each frame to SVS stack. Then, sending the detentions back to for visualization. From this <https:\\/\\/applied-home.slack.com\\/archives\\/C08K6CTGCDS\\/p1778041880644039?thread_ts=1778027036.696279&cid=C08K6CTGCDS|thread>, <@U03T2GNQ0CF|JayM> has done this in the past. If so, I can pick up from where he left off.\\n2. Model training pipeline: Take ADP data and convert it to a bag. Send those bags off to a model training pipeline, which is already in use on real data. After talking with <@U09DVKBSKMZ|Sohum> and <@U09BS4WKG94|Bala>, this is quite desirable right now (notes <https:\\/\\/docs.google.com\\/document\\/d\\/1Akz3sRL8dzgwh1MWbcEGlNVeSYirTAkypQ5Q-tgkskg\\/edit?tab=t.g2qma5ucvueg#heading=h.q0hpdrjenjmm|here>).\\n\\nimo, option 2 is easier but option 1 is much more impressive to the customer. <@U03T2GNQ0CF|JayM> can you weigh in on the state of option 1? <@U09DVKBSKMZ|Sohum>\\/<@U09BS4WKG94|Bala>, can you weigh in on which option is more directly useful to your team?\\n\\ncc <@U063Y6FQA5V|AlexD>\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Result 7 of 10\\nChannel: #program-komatsu (ID: C0961E7856J)\\nFrom: Alex Del Re (ID: U063Y6FQA5V) \\nTime: 2026-05-12 09:29:48 PDT\\nMessage_ts: 1778603388.421509\\nPermalink: [link](https:\\/\\/grid-appliedint.enterprise.slack.com\\/archives\\/C0961E7856J\\/p1778603388421509?thread_ts=1778515479.425979&cid=C0961E7856J)\\nText: \\nVirtual Toolchain \\n\\u2022 :status_green: Deliver Developer Studio SIL virtualizations to enable inter-zonal testing for Autolube and Engine Interface applications\\n    \\u25e6 Planning to host Peoria SIL testing workshop next week for autolube testing\\n\\u2022 :large_yellow_circle: Integrate SVS software with ADP sensor simulations\\n    \\u25e6 <@U07AY0G968H|Andrew McGovern> going to meet in <@U09DVKBSKMZ|Sohum> to discuss process\\n\\u2022 :status_green: Enhance the CI\\/CD pipeline to accelerate developer velocity, improving reliability, and enable consistent resource access\\n    \\u25e6 Added upstream back to core-stack functionality\\n    \\u25e6 adding workbench CI testing \\n\\u2022 :large_yellow_circle: Enable Machine Learning team to generate synthetic data &amp; evaluate performance change on ODS on oblique angle scenarios\\n    \\u25e6 Scoping a synthetic datasets workshop for next week\\n    \\u25e6 Planning to discuss with <@U06EB2G5EGM|Sergey> on Data Engine pipeline options for Komatsu team\\n\\u2022 :status_green: Validate synthetic sensors with Komatsu lab data to understand object detection metrics in different environmental conditions\\n    \\u25e6 <@U07AY0G968H|Andrew McGovern> reviewing with sensor validation team to discuss \\n\\u2022 :status_green: Develop 830E TruckSim model to enable Smart AHT controls simulation testing\\n    \\u25e6 Received 830E model parameters and working with TruckSim to team to create braking model for SDV SW application testing\\n    \\u25e6 Steering model development will occur after the braking model\\n\\u2022 :large_yellow_circle: Define plan to integrate 930E TruckSim model with steering and braking applications for SDV SW team\\n    \\u25e6 Planning to start this during 2026.21 sprint\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Result 8 of 10\\nChannel: #program-komatsu-surround-view-system (ID: C08K6CTGCDS)\\nFrom: Andrew McGovern (ID: U07AY0G968H) \\nTime: 2026-05-05 17:24:01 PDT\\nMessage_ts: 1778027041.427069\\nPermalink: [link](https:\\/\\/grid-appliedint.enterprise.slack.com\\/archives\\/C08K6CTGCDS\\/p1778027041427069?thread_ts=1778027036.696279&cid=C08K6CTGCDS)\\nText: \\nI'm in contact with <@U099CFQ3PL6|Aravind APS> from Komatsu. He is interested in setting up some HIL simulations for the SVS workstream. The tl;dr is that his goal is to \\\"send synthetic camera data from ADP to a perception module in real-time\\\". Here is the <https:\\/\\/applied-home.slack.com\\/archives\\/C09LSNE9Q0Y\\/p1771959337037149?thread_ts=1771959295.181759&cid=C09LSNE9Q0Y|thread>.\\n\\nAFAIK, the SVS stack isn't even integrated with ADP at all. Aravind also claims that he has tested sending synthetic ADP images through the SVS stack already. I feel like Aravind's request is not at all related to the current efforts. <@U09DVKBSKMZ|Sohum>, do you have any context here?\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Result 9 of 10\\nChannel: #program-komatsu-surround-view-system (ID: C08K6CTGCDS)\\nFrom: Andrew McGovern (ID: U07AY0G968H) \\nTime: 2026-05-28 09:54:04 PDT\\nMessage_ts: 1779987244.760379\\nPermalink: [link](https:\\/\\/grid-appliedint.enterprise.slack.com\\/archives\\/C08K6CTGCDS\\/p1779987244760379?thread_ts=1779821907.275389&cid=C08K6CTGCDS)\\nText: \\nBased on the discussion in <https:\\/\\/applied-home.slack.com\\/archives\\/C08K6CTGCDS\\/p1779918506691699?thread_ts=1779916420.875339&cid=C08K6CTGCDS|this thread>, the model training pipeline is likely going to be out of scope for this release (eng of june). Therefore, I will begin moving towards integrating the SVS inference with ADP. <@U09BS4WKG94|Bala>, put down 15 mins with you today to kick off this work\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Result 10 of 10\\nChannel: #program-komatsu-eng (ID: C09651DRWJE)\\nFrom: Ting Lu (ID: U056B308XB2) \\nTime: 2026-04-24 11:14:51 PDT\\nMessage_ts: 1777054491.798409\\nPermalink: [link](https:\\/\\/grid-appliedint.enterprise.slack.com\\/archives\\/C09651DRWJE\\/p1777054491798409?thread_ts=1776984393.946539&cid=C09651DRWJE)\\nText: \\n> What came out of your conversation with Brian in terms of ML scoping?\\n1. Enable model training in the shared repo, grant Komatsu engineers accesses so that they can use the pipeline and workflows\\n2. How sensorsim can fill the gap where data collection is challenging, how Komatsu team can make meaningful contributions \\n\\n> What would it actually look like to consume synthetic data output and feed it into the ODS pipeline?\\nIf you refer to onboard ODS pipeline, we didn't talk about it. The convo was about offboard synthetic data usage for model training and eval, <https:\\/\\/applied-home.slack.com\\/archives\\/C0APY81BA67\\/p1776118777331429|this thread> provides you context on converting the data clips to lance for ML training\\n\\n> How do we want to evaluate model performance?\\n<https:\\/\\/applied-home.slack.com\\/archives\\/C08REEEU86L\\/p1776894844208549|This thread> and <https:\\/\\/docs.google.com\\/document\\/d\\/1HatFMp_sm8GB6mCUydSLja8cQpdvaKKDd0YvGLHaFrk\\/edit?usp=sharing|the doc> give you the latest for model perf. e.g. IoU is used as an option for matching gate to calculate class-wise AP metrics\\n\\n---\\n\\n\",\"pagination_info\":\"For the next page of results use cursor `Q1VSUkVOVF9QQUdFOjI=`\\n\"}"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01AeQvEvhszVJhWytvQBSm5n","session_id":"e608aebc-1e8f-4a54-bfcc-c9052cb98c4e","uuid":"9449457a-8813-49bc-91a1-714bded14445","timestamp":"2026-06-01T17:05:44.368Z","subagent_type":"general-purpose","task_description":"Research ROSbag/MCAP format for ADP pipeline"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01BZrmHzmjijSReRtkviJEWX","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I now have a comprehensive picture. Here is the research report:\n\n---\n\n## Q1: What is the exact ROSbag/MCAP format spec for converting ADP outputs to the perception module training pipeline?\n\n### Answer\n\nThe ROSbag/MCAP format spec for ADP-to-perception-pipeline conversion is **not yet finalized**. This was confirmed directly in the June 1, 2026 office hours thread in #ext-program-katana-toolchain, where Andrew McGovern wrote post-call:\n\n> \"Data Engine pipeline still being built on Applied side. Eventually, this ADP data will need to be written to a ROS bag. These message definitions are not yet set in stone. Once they are, we can begin converting this ADP data into ROS bag.\"\n\nThis matches Alex Del Re's statement from the meeting verbatim (\"I need to track down if that is set in stone yet\").\n\nThe interim plan (also from that same June 1 thread) is to:\n1. Commit existing scripts into the `vehicle-os-katana` repo at `/katana/katana_adp` in a new folder.\n2. Focus on generating datasets with occlusions and weather conditions in the meantime.\n\nA separate but related data format path has already been validated: as of May 27, 2026 (meeting: \"Katana synthetic scenario and ML workflow\"), Applied's MLRL training pipeline already supports the **Lance format**, and 10k labeled frames in Lance format were ready from the sensor sim team. Andrew McGovern's action item from that meeting was to coordinate with Chunu's sensor sim team on an **ADP-to-Lance export** pipeline for SVS distorted cameras, and to evaluate promoting that conversion to a standard product export option. This is a working (or near-working) path that does not require ROSbag conversion and appears to be the more near-term viable route.\n\nAdditionally, as of May 28, 2026 (Toolchain Weekly Sync), Andrew McGovern had a separate \"data engine conversion script\" ready to migrate to the VOS Katana repo - the context there is for the 3D bounding box model training pipeline.\n\n### Sources\n\n- **#ext-program-katana-toolchain thread, June 1, 2026** (Andrew McGovern post-call notes): https://grid-appliedint.enterprise.slack.com/archives/C09LSNE9Q0Y/p1780330951672899 - Explicit confirmation that ROS bag message definitions are not yet set in stone; interim focus is script commits and dataset generation.\n\n- **AlexD DM notes, May 27, 2026** (\"Katana synthetic scenario and ML workflow\" meeting): https://grid-appliedint.enterprise.slack.com/archives/D0651MWAD4Y/p1779923258139899 - Lance format confirmed as MLRL-supported; ADP-to-Lance export is the active near-term path for SVS training.\n\n- **#program-komatsu-surround-view-system, May 26, 2026** (Andrew McGovern framing of two options): https://grid-appliedint.enterprise.slack.com/archives/C08K6CTGCDS/p1779821914224589 - Lays out Option 2 (ADP data to bag, then into existing model training pipeline) as desirable but deprioritized relative to open-loop inference integration.\n\n- **AlexD DM notes, May 28, 2026** (Toolchain Weekly Sync): https://grid-appliedint.enterprise.slack.com/archives/D0651MWAD4Y/p1780002494574089 - \"Data engine conversion script ready to migrate to VOS Katana\" referenced.\n\n- **KATA JIRA** - No KATA tickets found specifically for ROSbag or MCAP format spec for ADP synthetic data conversion.\n\n### Gaps\n\n1. **The ROS topic list is undefined.** No Slack discussion has yet produced a concrete set of ROS message types or topic names for the ADP-to-ROSbag conversion. The spec is on Applied's side (owned by the Data Engine team), not yet communicated to the Komatsu team.\n\n2. **Ownership of the message definitions** is unclear: the Data Engine team (Sergey's team, per prior references) appears to be the group responsible, but no DRI has been named for the spec itself.\n\n3. **Lance vs. ROSbag divergence**: The SVS training pipeline is currently moving toward Lance format (which MLRL already supports), while the ROSbag path is blocked on undefined message definitions. It is not confirmed whether these are parallel approaches or whether one will supersede the other.\n\n4. **Suggested follow-up**: Ask Andrew McGovern directly who on the Data Engine team owns the ROS message definition spec, and whether the Lance-format path (already working with 10k frames) can fully substitute for the ROSbag path for SVS model training purposes."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6035,"cache_read_input_tokens":57391,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":6035,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01AeQvEvhszVJhWytvQBSm5n","session_id":"e608aebc-1e8f-4a54-bfcc-c9052cb98c4e","uuid":"faf1a2da-8b5f-48db-a4cc-119b374f84af","request_id":"req_011CbcuR7nstR5oPpvqXUATp","subagent_type":"general-purpose","task_description":"Research ROSbag/MCAP format for ADP pipeline"}
